title: gazpacho
directions: Place the carrots, cucumbers, green bell peppers and tomatoes in the bowl of a food processor; process just until chunky (you may need to do it in two batches).
Transfer the mixture to a large bowl; season with the cilantro, salt, cumin and dill weed (you may want to add more, to taste).
Chill for at least 2 hours. Serve with a dollop of sour cream and a sprinkling of cumin. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: zimtsterne(cinnamon stars)
directions: Whip egg whites with electric beater, starting at low speed. Add cream of tartar and sugar.
Beat until peaks (soft) are formed. Beat 15 minutes at medium speed.
Put one cup mixture aside; this will be used for glaze.
Fold in ground pecans with a wooden spoon. Heat oven to 275°.
Bake on cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Drop by teaspoon on paper.
Use reserved egg whites as a glaze. Garnish with a 1/2 pecan or Hug candy or can be left plain.
Bake 20 minutes.
Glaze should be light brown, but soft.
Slide paper on a table which has been moistened with water.
Lift cookies gently with spatula.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Vegetables should be a mixture of broccoli, cauliflower and carrots, thawed and drained.
Combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter in saucepan; heat over medium heat until melted and smooth, stir often.
Place vegetables in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over casserole and mix well.
Melt remaining butter and mix with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Temperature: 375°.
Time: 20 minutes.
Servings: 18 biscuits at 1 1/2-inches, 12 biscuits at 2-inches.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter and eggs in a large pan.
Add chopped nuts and fruits.
Line cake pans with brown paper and grease paper.
Put a pan of water in the oven while baking.
Will fill 2 angel food cake tins.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.
Remove from pans.
Wrap with cheesecloth and soak.

title: rum custard pie
directions: Beat 4 egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add hot water slowly and cook in double boiler until thick.
Add one envelope of gelatin dissolved in cold water and stir; cool.
Add 1/4 cup rum and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Beat egg whites gradually adding 1/2 cup sugar.
When custard has thickened, fold in egg whites.
Line pie pan with graham crackers.
Pour in custard mixture.
Top with 1/2 pint whipped cream.
Place in refrigerator until cold.
Top with grated unsweetened chocolate.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Blend in flour until smooth. Slowly stir in chicken broth and pepper; simmer for a few minutes. Add milk gradually.
Stirring constantly, cook slowly until thickened.
Do not boil.
Add crab meat and salt to taste.
Remove from heat.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Saute onions and bell peppers.
Mash up chili beans.
Add taco sauce.
Add peppers and cheese.
Add chili powder, if desired.

title: b & b relish
directions: Mix together tomatoes, onions, peppers and salt.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours.
Mix together sugar and vinegar.
Pour over tomato mixture.
Heat through and seal in jars.
Do not cook.

title: dewy apple dumplins
directions: Microwave peeled/quartered apples, cinnamon and nutmeg for 2 to 4 minutes to start them softening. Roll 1 slice of apple in 1 crescent roll. Place all in a sprayed 11 x 17 pan. Melt butter and mix with sugar, vanilla and trailings of cinnamon and nutmeg. Pour over dumplings and then pour 1 can of Mountain Dew over whole thing. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, until brown and bubbly.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers, in a large bowl.
Add crackers; stir and keep mixing until crackers are all covered. Can be eaten right away or stored until later.
Store in an airtight container.

title: quick tomato sauce(good with meatballs and spaghetti)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until glazed.
Add tomatoes, herbs, tomato paste and wine.
Simmer for at least 1/2 hour.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: easy rhubarb cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package. Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Top with rhubarb and sprinkle sugar over rhubarb. Put whipping cream over all and bake as directed on cake box.

title: egg custard
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Pour in margarine and stir.
Add milk, vanilla and beaten eggs and stir. (Stir in coconut, if desired.)
Pour into greased and floured baking dish (9 x 11-inch) and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: beef dip for chips
directions: Cream the cream cheese and milk.
Spread in a 2-inch serving dish.
Brown ground beef and taco seasoning.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Mix onion, tomatoes and green chilies.
Spread over meat.
Sprinkle cheese over top.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring sugar, margarine, syrup and salt to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes on High in microwave oven.
Remove from oven and stir in soda.
Put popcorn in a large brown bag.
Pour syrup over popcorn. Fold top of bag and place in microwave on High for 4 to 4 1/2 minutes.
Remove bag from oven every 45 to 50 seconds and shake. Spread caramel coated corn on waxed paper to cool.
Store tightly covered.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken and cool.
Chop chicken and add remaining ingredients.
Mix and chill.
Use on croissants or just plain bread.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well all the ingredients and pour mixture into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: soap bubbles
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape pipe cleaners into a circle with a handle.
Blow bubbles through the pipe cleaner loop.
This is great fun!

title: marinade for meat
directions: Mix and pour over meat.
Let set overnight.
Cut meat (chicken breast or steak) in about 1-inch pieces.
Place meat, bell peppers, onions and mushrooms on skewers.
Cook meat on grill.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Boil shrimp with garlic and salt in 3 cups of water for 4 to 5 minutes; drain, reserving liquid.
Shell and devein shrimp. Return shells to reserved cooking liquid and boil down until liquid measures 1 1/2 cups.
Strain and reserve broth.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Place marshmallows,
chocolate	chips,	Hershey bar and walnuts in largest mixing
bowl.
Place in saucepan the evaporated milk, sugar and butter
and
boil 6 minutes.
Be sure to boil exactly 6 minutes from beginning rolling boil.
Pour over ingredients in bowl,
beating (mixing briskly) until marshmallows and chocolate are
dissolved.
Pour in large buttered pan and cool. Store in closed container.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Alternate potatoes, onion and cheese in an 8 x 10-inch greased baking dish.
After one layer of potatoes, onion and cheese, pour on 1/2 of soup mixture.
Add the rest of the potatoes, onion and cheese.
Top with remaining soup mixture.
Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: baked grecian chicken
directions: Make an opening in side of each piece of chicken.
Place a piece of cheese inside opening.
Spread mayonnaise lightly on each piece of chicken.
Mix crumbs and onion soup mix.
Roll chicken in crumbs.
Place on rack in baking pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand a while before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into small pieces.
Butter a Bundt pan with lots of butter.
Place a layer of biscuits, then sprinkle the raisins, sugar, cinnamon and nut mixture.
Place another layer of biscuits, then mixture, until all is used.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°. Tip down at once.
Pinch off bite size pieces to eat.

title: butter flakes
directions: Scald milk.
Combine with shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm .
Add yeast and stir well.
Add eggs, then flour and milk to make a smooth, soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Place dough in warm, but not hot, greased bowl.
Cover and place in warm, dry place.
Avoid drafts and let rise until doubled in bulk.

title: johnny mazetti
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add chopped onion, celery and peppers. Mix together and pour in large casserole.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over meat mixture.
Top with grated cheese. Cover and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.

title: cool fruit salad
directions: Whip cream and fold in fruits and marshmallows.
Mix powdered sugar and mayonnaise and add to fruit mixture.
Freeze in flat 9 x 10 inch pan.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: forgotten meringue cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small mixer bowl combine egg whites and salt.
At high speed, beat to soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar, continuing to beat at high speed until very stiff peaks form. Gently fold in chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop by half teaspoons onto 2 heavy greased cookie sheets.
Place sheets in oven. Immediately turn oven off!!!
Leave in oven overnight with oven door closed.
Do not peek.
Make before going to bed.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, and pour into pie shell. Decorate top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Add together in large roaster.
Place in oven at 350° for 4 1/2 to 5 hours, stirring frequently.
Put in jars.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: In large pot, put water and all seasonings.
Bring to boil. Add potatoes and onions.
Cook until potatoes and onions are fork-tender.
Add corn and cook about 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until slightly done.
Remove from heat and let set about 15 minutes for seasoning to go through shrimp and vegetables.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops; place in casserole dish.
Place onions on chops; sprinkle with salt.
Add rice on top.
Combine soups; pour over rice.
Add water.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Beat in blender.
Keep refrigerated. Shake well when serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Put in ovensafe container. Add topping.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt margarine, adding seasoned salt or onion salt and chili powder.
Use a large flat roaster pan, top and bottom.
Drizzle mixture over top of cereal mixture in each the top and bottom of the roaster pan.
Bake in 250° oven for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight containers.

title: candy bar fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with buttered foil.

In a large microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate and butterscotch chips. Microwave on Medium for 1 to 2 minutes or until melted. Stir until smooth. Stir in frosting and all but 2 tablespoons of candy bar until mixed.
Spread in foil lined pan. Sprinkle with reserved candy bar.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.
Remove fudge by lifting foil. Remove foil from fudge and cut into squares.

title: skillet turkey dinner
directions: Cook sausage in a large skillet coated with cooking spray until browned; drain.
Add garlic and remaining ingredients, tossing gently.
Cover and cook over medium heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sifted dry ingredients.
Make well in center.
Add eggs, carrots and oil.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: grape juice wine
directions: Let the yeast and water stand a little.
Mix juice, sugar and some water together in a bowl to melt sugar a little, then add yeast mixture.
Pour into a clean glass vinegar jug.
Fill with water to neck of jug to make 1 gallon.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt.
Place in greased baking pan.
Combine soup and sour cream and drop on each chicken breast.
Sprinkle with crackers and poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: apple crisp
directions: Lay apples in buttered cake pan.
Combine sugar, salt, 1 tablespoon flour and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Mix oatmeal, baking powder, 3/4 cup flour, brown sugar, baking soda and butter.
Mix together until crumbly.
Put over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender and top is browned.

title: sparkling berry salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, sprinkle unflavored gelatin over 1 cup cranberry-raspberry juice and let stand 1 minute. Stir over low heat until gelatin in completely dissolved, about 5 minutes. Stir in sugar until dissolved.

In a large bowl, blend remaining 1 cup cranberry-raspberry juice, soda, gelatin mixture, lemon juice and orange peel. Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites, about 60 minutes. Fold in berries.
Pour into 6-cup bowl or mold.
Chill about 3 hours. Serve with sour cream, if desired.

title: diabetic whipped topping
directions: Chill small bowl and beaters. Combine dry milk with ice water and beat until stiff. Add vanilla and sugar. Serve immediately.

title: chicken loaf *
directions: Chop chicken into small pieces; add remaining ingredients as given.
Place in a greased loaf pan and bake in oven until firm, 25 to 30 minutes.
This loaf may be mixed and placed into pans, covered well and frozen until ready to use.
Bake just before serving.

title: red velvet gooey cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 9 x 13 baking dish with cooking spray. Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg together and pat into pan.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown flour in bacon drippings.
Add water and tomato paste, making a thin mixture.
Fry onions and garlic then add all the ingredients and mix with flour and tomato mixture.	Cook for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and cook for 20 minutes until shrimp is cooked (do not overcook shrimp or it will be tough).	Serve on rice.	You can omit red pepper and use black pepper.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, water, oil and eggs.
Beat well. Blend in sour cream.
Put chocolate chips and flour in a bag and shake to coat.
Add to cake batter.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and chill. Served with sliced fruit.

title: quiche lorraine(portuguese)
directions: Prepare pastry. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onions in pastry lined pie plate. Beat eggs slightly. Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour egg mixture into pie plate.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy shrimp nachos
directions: Butter flour tortillas and sprinkle crab and/or shrimp on top. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven, 8 to 10 minutes, on a cookie sheet.
Two tortillas fit fine on one cookie sheet.

title: francis ingram's corn bread recipe
directions: Dump all the dry ingredients into a bowl and stir them well. Then form a little hole with your spoon and break the egg; pour the buttermilk into it.

Mix well, then pour into a hot skillet that you've melted a tablespoon or two of bacon drippings in. Leave the skillet on the burner for a minute or so, then put it in a preheated oven (400°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
It's done when you knock on the top and it sounds hollow.
This will dump out of the skillet easily and have a nice golden crust on the bottom.

title: mountain meadow pork chops
directions: Slice garlic thinly; place inside slits in pork chops.
Brown quickly in olive oil.
Spread mustard over pork chops, add apples and water; put on medium and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 (or 2 very hungry people).
Serve with wild rice.

title: seafood dip
directions: Stir cream cheese until slightly softened.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: lima beans(germany)
directions: Boil the beans, and when almost done add the potatoes (peeled and diced).
When finished, add paprika, milk and butter.
Serve hot.

title: crock pot green beans and potatoes
directions: Cube potatoes with skin on into 3/4 inch cubes.
If potatoes are small, leave whole.
Leave green beans whole.
Cut links in half. In crock pot, layer potatoes, beans, links, tomatoes and then broth.
DO NOT MIX TOGETHER!!!
Cook on high 4 hours or until done. Season to taste.

title: snappy turtle cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Heat over boiling water until chocolate melts.
Blend until smooth.
Remove from heat and ice.

title: cajun skillet hash
directions: In large skillet, cook onion and garlic in butter until tender-crisp.
Add	potatoes
and
cook
2	minutes.
Stir	in tomatoes and thyme; simmer 2 to 3 minutes.	Add meat and green pepper.
Season
with
salt
and
pepper
to
taste.
Simmer, stirring frequently,
to 5 minutes.
Season with hot pepper sauce, if
desired.
If
using original style stewed tomatoes, add a pinch each of cinnamon, ground cloves and cayenne.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and coconut together well.
Add 1/2 of milk and eggs.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sweetheart cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place paper liners in cupcake tins. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Beat at low speed for about 1 minute, until mix is moistened, then beat at high speed for 2 additional minutes.
Fill cupcake tins 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned and center springs back when touched lightly.
Let cool on wire racks. Place a bit of all fruit preserves or a tablespoon of pudding on top of each cupcake.
Makes 24 cupcakes with 95 calories and 3 grams of fat each.

title: freezer pie crust
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in large bowl.
Then mix the remaining ingredients together in another bowl, then add to first bowl.
Form into 4 parts.
Use immediately or freeze for another time.
Makes 4 single crusts.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook one hour and can.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine the granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit into 4 parts.
Roll the pieces of biscuits in the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place them in a Teflon-coated cake layer pan.
Pour the brown sugar and butter mixture over the biscuit pieces.
Place in oven for approximately 15 minutes.
Delicious hot!

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine 3/4 cup cheese, corn, evaporated milk, eggs and onions together in 1-quart casserole dish.
Toss bread crumbs with butter and remaining cheese; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with green pepper rings.

title: forever wedding cake
directions: Mix with a pint of sympathy.
Sprinkle with forgiveness as often as necessary.
Warm by a bright fireside with loving kisses. Repeat as desired.

title: pineapple cream cheese pastries
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together, then add flour.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Shape dough into a ball and chill.
Roll out 1 part at a time and cut into squares.
Place 1/2 teaspoon filling in center and fold over to seal.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hearty baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion.
Add sausage and brown lightly.
Mix with remaining ingredients in large baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 1 hour or so.

title: thanksgiving pumpkin crunch
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with wax paper.
Mix first 5 ingredients and pour in pan.
Shake dry cake mix and nuts over this. Dribble melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool, invert pan, remove wax paper and top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.
"Better than pumpkin pie".

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Place shortening and salt in boiling water; let stand until lukewarm. Beat eggs and mix in sugar.
Add to water mixture and add yeast.
Stir in 2 cups flour; beat well.
Add remaining flour gradually. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll dough in 2 rounds 1/4-inch thick. Spread with softened butter and cut in pie shaped wedges. Roll into crescents.
Let rise 3 hours on greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 6 to 10 minutes.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen rolls.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Combine 100% bran and water in a large bowl and set aside. In another large bowl, cream the sugar, shortening and eggs, using electric mixer.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Stir in bran and water mixture.
Store in refrigerator in tightly covered container.
Mixture will keep up to 6 weeks.

title: chinese chicken rolls(150 calories per serving)
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving, in small bowl, mix well cabbage, green onion, celery, soy sauce and ginger.

Set aside. On cutting board, cut each chicken breast lengthwise in half. With mallet or dull edge of French knife, between 2 sheets of waxed paper, pound chicken pieces to about 1/4-inch thickness. Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper on one side of each piece. Top each piece with 1/4 of cabbage mixture.
From a narrow end, roll each, jelly roll fashion and fasten with toothpicks.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Drain pineapple.
Add cold water to juice to make 1 cup.
Add to jello.
Add crushed pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Stir and congeal.

title: chili pie
directions: Put half of the corn chips in the bottom of a casserole dish. Place the tamales next and sprinkle the onions and half the cheese over them.
Mix a half can of water with your chili and pour it over the tamales.
Sprinkle the top of it with the rest of the chips and cheese.
Place in the oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: wild stir-fry chicken skillet
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken which has been cut into bite-size pieces and cook, stirring frequently, until firm and white.
Add chicken broth; stir. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until water is absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Stir in lettuce and tomatoes. Mushrooms and Chinese vegetables may be added to chick peas and onions if desired.

title: fruit spritzer
directions: Makes 27 (4 ounce) servings.

title: lime jellied salad supreme
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to gelatin.
Add pineapple and cool slightly.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Add nuts and cherries and pour into mold.
Let salad set overnite.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients into crumbs and take out 1 cup. Add rest of the ingredients and pour into a greased pan. Sprinkle the crumbs on top. Bake about 1/2 hour or until done.

title: marie's southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly (not to much).
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and melted butter.

title: self-crust peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in dish. In another bowl, mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder. Pour over melted margarine.
Pour peaches directly into center of mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the margarine.
Add salt, sugar and gradually add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift all-purpose flour, measure and sift with baking powder.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add grated rind of lemon.
Add chopped nuts and/or cherries.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.
While bread is baking, mix 1/2 cup sugar and juice of 1 lemon and allow to set.
Place bread pan on rack to cool.
While bread is hot, spoon the sugar and lemon juice mixture over the top.
Remove from pan.
Wrap and allow to mellow for 1 to 2 days.

title: mexican dip
directions: Put sour cream in bottom of dish.
Chop green onions, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Put on top of sour cream.
Add shredded cheese on top.
Add salsa right before serving.
Great served with nacho chips.

title: rusks(kavringer)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
On a lightly floured pastry board roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut 2-inch rounds.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400° until brown.
Split each biscuit in half and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 200° for about 5 minutes or until light brown. Makes 4 dozen.
Can be frozen.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.

Set aside to cool. Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each. Add cooled chocolate and vanilla. Sift flour, salt and soda together. Add alternately with buttermilk. Beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into three 9-inch greased and floured round cake pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Ice with Coconut-Pecan Frosting.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Place chicken breasts in a foiled lined pan or baking dish. Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.
Take out and pour desired amount of dressing on chicken, bake 20 more minutes.
Turn and pour remaining dressing on chicken and bake 20 more minutes or until done.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Beat all ingredients except pecans until smooth, 30 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Fold in chopped pecans.
Pour into greased pie plate and bake in preheated 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Insert knife and if it is clean, the pie is done.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one by one.
To this, add salt and the juice and rind of lemons.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake until browned.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Cook ground
beef
in
oil until redness leaves.
Remove from pan and cook onions, macaroni and pepper in same pan until macaroni is
yellow.
Add
the beef, tomato sauce, water, black pepper, salt
and
Worcestershire
sauce
to
the onions, green pepper and
macaroni.
Let
simmer 25 minutes or until macaroni is cooked.
Serves 8.

title: cracker crappie
directions: You will need a thick bottom frying pan.

title: deviled clams
directions: Grind eggs, onion, celery and raw clams.
Mix bread crumbs, milk or juice from clams, butter, parsley and pepper all together. Put mixture into halved shells and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
This also freezes well unbaked in shells.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill several hours before serving with raw vegetables.
Keeps for weeks in refrigerator.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Reduce cider to 1 cup by boiling.
Combine and stir all ingredients in crock-pot and cook, uncovered, 6 to 8 hours on high setting.
One teaspoon of cinnamon is enough.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put Bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper into a Baggie, then add the chicken in and shake (2 pieces at a time).
Shake until coated. Put skin side down in a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Potatoes may be baked at the same time.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: The night before or early in the day on which you wish to serve the salad, slice alternate layers of sweet onion and cucumber, sprinkling salt between each layer.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator to wilt.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown meat with salt in skillet without shortening.
Mix remaining ingredients, except noodles; add to meat.
Stir well; put in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 2 hours at 275°. Put noodles on top the last 15 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: streusel topped fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spoon pie filling into pastry shell. In bowl, combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly; stir in nuts.
Crumble over pie filling.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until top is golden and filling is bubbly. Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cream pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, milk and sugar and cook over medium heat until mixture begins to thicken.
Add a small portion of mixture to egg yolks.
Beat and add back to mixture.
When completely thickened, remove from fire and add salt and vanilla.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together egg and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt, then add to egg mixture.
To this, add the drained fruit cocktail and vanilla.
Spread in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix together brown sugar and chopped nuts and sprinkle over batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Lightly salt and cover with chicken.
Mix mayonnaise, soup and lemon juice.
Spread over chicken and broccoli.
Spread with cheese.
Combine cracker crumbs and butter. Spread over all.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake for diabetics
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is gone.
Add the applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Blend in the other ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add vanilla. Pour into loaf pans, sprayed with Pam.
Use foil liners, also sprayed with Pam.
Bake about 1 hour in a 350° oven or until done. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: stately scallops
directions: Saute scallops in butter in large skillet for 3 minutes or until tender.
Remove scallops from skillet and reserve drippings. Saute mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Remove and reserve drippings. Add wine, juices and seasonings to skillet.
Bring to a boil and cook 8 minutes.
Add scallops and vegetables.
Heat thoroughly. Serve over hot vermicelli.

title: swedish meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, egg, stuffing, nutmeg and 1/3 cup soup. Shape firmly into loaf; place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: watermelon jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl.

Pour mixture slowly into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm. Dip bottom of pan in warm water for 15 seconds to loosen gelatin. Cut shapes with cookie cutters all the way through gelatin.
Lift from pan with fingers or metal spatula.
Makes 24 pieces or 4 to 6 servings.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Place all ingredients into a deep pot and simmer for 2 hours.
May use crock-pot. Serve with mashed potatoes and biscuits.

title: glazed fruit
directions: Drain pineapple and keep the juice.
Drain oranges.
Sprinkle bananas with Fruit Fresh and slice into medium slices.
Mix the fruit.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Pour off most of the grease.
Break eggs in a bowl and pour over bacon.
Stir like scrambled eggs. Add water, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat until all liquid is hot.
Break up lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Add onion cut into bite-size pieces and then pour the mixture over lettuce. Stir well.
We serve with potatoes cooked in salt water.

title: raspberry cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients (sugar, flour, baking powder, oleo and milk) and put in ungreased baking dish (8 x 12). Cover with fruit. Over fruit, sprinkle 1 cup sugar. Then pour over all the boiling water or juice. Bake at 375° about 60 minutes.

title: shrimp and wild rice casserole
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and bake in covered casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Melt 1 stick of butter and saute shrimp, onions and mushrooms.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Combine cooked rice and sauteed mixture; blend well and serve.

title: frosty fruit cooler
directions: Using 4 quart nonmetal container, combine all juices.
Stir in lemon-lime and float scoops of sherbet on top.

title: cheese corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and toss in grated cheese.
Beat eggs until mixed and stir in milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir in melted margarine and butter flavoring.
Bake in greased pan at 425° for about 25 minutes or until brown.

title: special chicken cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Chop
chicken
and mix all ingredients together.
Shape in a ball. May be rolled in chopped nuts. Serve with Chicken in a Biskit crackers.
Enjoy!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In skillet, cook first 6 ingredients until broccoli and onion are soft.
In a casserole dish, put cooked rice.
Bake all of this in the oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Beat egg until light and fluffy.
Add juice of lemon and powdered sugar.
In top of double boiler, cook until thickened. Cover and cool.
This is the basic cream which may be folded into any of the following for a light and luscious fruit salad topping. Add to 1 cup sour cream, 1 cup mayonnaise or 1/2 pint whipping cream, whipped.

title: honey of a fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter. Add cornstarch and cocoa. Blend. Add honey and water.

Cook over low heat stirring constantly until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Remove from heat. Add marshmallows. Stir until melted. Stir in vanilla. Serve over ice cream, warm or cold. Make 2 1/2 cups.

title: freezer biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to milk.
Add milk to dry ingredients and mix well.
Turn onto floured board.
Roll out and cut.
Freeze on baking sheet.
After frozen, store in freezer.
Dip in melted butter and bake at 400°.

title: easy, easy fudge cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cook pudding according to directions.
Stir in dry cake mix.
Pour into pan and top with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.	Pour into 3 greased and floured 8 or 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt butter and flour together; brown just a bit.
Add broth and milk; stir until bubbly.
Add the cheese, pimentos and bacon bits at the last.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients and make into patties. Brown on both sides.
Drain off grease.
Lay in layers in cake pan.
Take remaining soup, Worcestershire sauce and mustard, mix together and pour over patties.
Cover with foil and bake slowly for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a bowl.
In a boiler, melt butter over low heat.
Add sugar/cocoa mixture to melted butter.
Stir good. Add milk and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Add pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper or pour into a 9 x 5 buttered Pyrex dish. Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 24 pieces.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Salt and pepper tops. Spread soup over top of chicken.
Place mushroom pieces between breasts so they don't dry out as they cook.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spread cheese over top and melt for about 5 minutes.
Serve over wild rice.

title: ice cream french vanilla
directions: Beat and pour into freezer can of ice cream maker.
Follow directions on your ice cream maker.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar, butter, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until creamy.
Mix in flour.
Mix until dough leaves sides of pan.
Form into balls; flatten with hands or fork.
Bake about 9 to 11 minutes or until edges become lightly brown.

title: dutch cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let raise until double in size and then divide into five 9-inch round pans and let raise again until double in size.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not stick with a fork.

title: chicken breasts sauteed in butter
directions: Season the breasts with salt and pepper.
Dredge them in flour and shake off excess.
Set the frying pan over high heat.
Add the butter.
Lay in chicken breasts.
Saute 1 minute on each side.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Arrange fish in a flat baking dish which has been buttered. Add a few sprinkles of pepper if desired.
Dot fillets with butter.
Spread soup over fish and sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: aunt patty's potatoes
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and add a dash of salt and pepper. Put into greased 9 x 13 pan and top with corn flakes mixed with 1/2 stick of butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt together oleo and cocoa.
Mix flour, pecans, eggs, sugar and coconut.
Mix all together and bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread 1 pint marshmallow cream on top.

title: bachelor's dinner
directions: Pour bag of Doritos into large bowl.
Remove mug from freezer. Allow to frost.
Set up T.V. tray by lounge chair.
Pour beer (pop may be substituted) into mug.
Proceed to chair, sit down and turn on favorite channel.
Usually served with football games, but any sports oriented show will do.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Arrange in baking dish (need 13 x 9 x 2-inch size).
Place chicken baked and deboned on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until good and bubbly!
(Otherwise, may not be hot enough in middle.)

title: the best honey whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast into 1/2 cup water.
Stir in honey, shortening, salt, 1 3/4 cups water and whole wheat flour.
Beat until smooth. Mix in bread flour until easy to handle.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes until soft and pliable.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover for 1 hour until doubled.
Using clean cloth, punch down.
Divide in half and shape each half in individual greased pans.
Let rise until dough is 1-inch above rim of pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: roast
directions: Stuff garlic cloves in roast. Rub roast with flour and pepper on all sides. Brown roast on all sides. Mix cream of mushroom soup, Lipton soup mix and water. Pour over roast. Add carrots and potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook rice with water and curry powder as directed on package, omitting butter.
Cool; add dressing, chicken, onion and celery. Refrigerate to blend flavors.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: Prepare pudding as directed using very cold milk.
When pudding is thick, fold in Cool Whip.
Put into dessert dishes and top with additional Cool Whip and nuts.
Serves 4.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Then add all but last 3.
Add them last.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan or make 2 or 3 layers and bake for 20 minutes.
Frost layers with Uncooked Fudge Frosting.

title: joy's* pasta with chicken and broccoli
directions: *As in Joy Philbin, Regis' wife.

title: diabetic sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks; add water, sweetener, vanilla and lemon juice. Beat until thick and fluffy, about 8 minutes.
Add flour and salt gradually, mixing well.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; beat until stiff.
Fold batter into egg whites until blended.
Bake in ungreased loaf pan about 1 hour at 325°, until done.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix salt, pepper and flour, pounding this into chuck steak. Brown steak in fat.
Slice onion over steak.
Add green pepper and 1 1/2 cups tomato juice.
Cook slowly for approximately 2 hours. Twenty minutes before steak is done, add mushrooms.
Serves 5.

title: lemon pecan cake
directions: Cream butter;
gradually add brown sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add
egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine
flour,
baking powder and salt; add to creamed
mixture
alternately
with milk, beginning and ending with flour
mixture.
Beat
well
after
each addition. Stir in lemon
extract and pecans. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Fold
into
batter.
Pour
batter
into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake
at
325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool
in
pan
for 15 minutes, remove from pan and cool completely.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
In large pan, mix remaining ingredients.
Add potatoes; mix lightly.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: nutty pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine 1st three ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat until sugar dissolves.
Add pumpkin and buttermilk; beat until smooth.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add pumpkin mixture stirring just to moisten dry ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin pans; fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: pumpkin indian pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Butter a 1-quart baking dish; set aside.
In a large, heavy saucepan, combine milk and cornmeal. Cook and stir over medium heat 7 to 10 minutes until the mixture is creamy.
Add butter and stir until melted.

title: peach cake
directions: Drain 2/3 of juice from peaches.
Put all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, then add egg and enough sweet milk to make thin batter.
Pour in hot well-greased bread pans or corn stick pans.
Bake until golden brown in a hot oven.
Mighty good with beans, sorghum molasses or about anything.

title: hurry up rolls
directions: "Our family cud wrap thair lips around one uv thez quickern' a spider cud catch a fly."

title: chicken waldorf salad(4 servings)
directions: Combine chicken, bean sprouts, carrots, celery, apple, raisins and walnuts in a separate bowl, stir ingredients remaining until blended.
Pour over salad; stir to coat.
Serve with whole wheat crackers or into a pita to make a complete meal.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in warm water.
In a separate bowl place lard, salt and sugar.
Pour boiling water over and stir until dissolved.
When lukewarm, add yeast with wire whisk.
Beat in egg. Stir in sifted flour to make a soft dough.
Place dough in a large bowl and cover with plate and put in refrigerator.
Chill from 2 to 12 hours.
Pinch off small pieces of dough with buttered hands. Place in greased muffin pans (preferably).
Fill 1/3 full and raise 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Blend everything but cookie dough.
Use half of cookie dough to slice and line bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour mixture over dough.
Slice remaining dough and line top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool completely before cutting.
Keep refrigerated.

title: streamlined white bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, salt, sugar and half the flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour and blend until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and cover with towel, let rise 30 minutes in warm place.
Punch down. Put in 2 loaf pans (greased), cover and let rise for 40 minutes. Bake until brown.

title: lima bean special
directions: Melt butter and add mushrooms.
Cool 5 minutes, then sprinkle with flour.
Slowly add 2 cups milk.
Stir and cook until sauce thickens.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add lima beans.
Gently reheat and serve hot.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, onions and Worcestershire sauce. Split bread down the top, being careful not to cut completely through.
Put spread on bread.
Top with paprika.
Wrap with foil, leaving top open.
May make and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat chopped pecans and Angel Flake coconut in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour on top of coconut.

title: sugarless cookies(adapted from american diabetes association)
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add orange juice, orange rind, oil and egg.
Mix well.
Add walnuts and raisins (raisins are chopped to add more sweetening power).
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls about 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in oven preheated to 375° about 15 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: sanchos
directions: Brown ground beef; mix in enchilada sauce and refried beans. Add chili seasoning, if desired.
Put in flour tortilla shells and fry until light brown.
Pour Ro-Tel cheese dip over them and top with chili beans and cheese.

title: cherry whip cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Spread in pan (will be very thick).
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: summertime punch with ice wreath
directions: A Day Ahead:
In medium bowl, mix 3 cups raspberry-cranberry drink and 2 cups water.
Pour 3 1/2 cups of this drink mixture into 6-cup ring mold; freeze.
Refrigerate the remaining 1 1/2 cups. Cut a continuous 1-inch wide strip of peel from each lemon and lime; reserve peels.
Squeeze juice from lemons and limes to equal 1/4 cup each.
Refrigerate to use in punch later.
Trim white membrane from lemon-lime peel strips.
Form each strip into a rose by rolling it tightly, skin side out, around finger; secure with a toothpick.
Cover; refrigerate.

title: lite double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin with wire whisk.
Mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: adobo(chicken and pork)
directions: Mix all ingredients into a pot.
Let stand an hour or even overnight.
Cook, covered, on medium-high heat until mixture boils.
Reduce heat to medium; turn meat and cook, covered, for one hour or until meat is tender and only a small amount of liquid is left.
Serves 6.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water. Bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup of the chocolate chips and vanilla extract.
Stir until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Mix crackers with melted butter.
Layer crackers alternately with oysters in casserole dish.
Mix cream, oyster liquid, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over cracker-oyster layers.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: roasted chicken with vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bag or bowl, put all the ingredients.
Shake in bag or toss in bowl until coated.
Empty into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, stirring twice, for 1 hour, or until chicken is done and vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Dates may be substituted for raisins.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Add dry ingredients.
Form into walnut size balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place on cookie sheet, but do not flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: extra moist pumpkin bread
directions: Bake in sprayed loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: easy scallop potatoes
directions: Use part of melted butter to grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan. Top with remaining butter. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hodge podge soup
directions: Cook hamburger; drain. Add soup, Ro-Tel, beans, tomato juice, salt, pepper and garlic to taste. Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: polynesian honey dip
directions: Place sour cream in blender.
Mix gradually.
Add brown sugar, mixing to blend.
Add honey and brandy.
Mix a couple of seconds longer.
Chill dip with cubes of coconut.

title: italian squash casserole
directions: Chop onions; slice green peppers in strips; cut squash and zucchini in circular 1/8-inch to 1/4-inch wide slices.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Boil raisins in strong coffee. Drain and dissolve soda in hot coffee. Cool.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand while mixing batter. Mix all ingredients together, except applesauce, oil, eggs, and milk.
Mix liquid ingredients thoroughly and add to dry ingredients and stir (don't overstir).
Pour into loaf pan and add topping (first 3 ingredients).
Bake at 350° for 55-60 minutes.

title: emily's spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain fat.
Add pepper and chili powder.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: diet chocolate delight(sugar-free)
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans in small bowl until well blended.
Add pecans and blend with spoon until pecans are well coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered dish or wax paper and chill.

title: butter bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with salt and pepper.
Simmer celery and chopped onions. Add the green beans, butter beans, soup and soy sauce.
Put in buttered 2-quart casserole and top with Tater Tots. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dunlap cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in layers for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick and water together.
Pat down in a rectangular pan (greased and floured).
Stir oregano and tomato sauce together; put over Bisquick mixture.
Add hamburger next.
Add layer of mushrooms.
Top with cheese, then pepperoni.
Bake at 350° until cheese is lightly browned.

title: spanish rice
directions: Form beef into patties and brown.
Put on paper towels. Drain any grease from skillet.
Cut onion into thin wedges.
Cut green peppers into stripes.
Saute onions and peppers until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Remove from skillet.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to directions on package for 15 minutes. Package directions tell when to add tomatoes.
Remove cover and add chopped patties and onions/peppers.
Stir and cover for about 5 more minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Reserve 1/2 tomato soup.
Mix all other ingredients thoroughly.
Place in large casserole.
Pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: meat salad
directions: Mix and fill pita or sandwich

title: crab meat stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms in water and drain.
Separate stems from caps, leaving caps intact.
Mince the stems finely.
Saute onion, stems and garlic in the butter.
Add crab meat.
Remove from heat and mix thoroughly.
Let cool.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet and sprinkle gently with paprika, if desired.
Place in 350° oven and leave for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: spencer's chili mac
directions: Simmer 1 hour or until celery is tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: raspberry or apricot dreams
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add butter, egg and milk. Beat until smooth.
Roll or pat into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread thin layer of jam.
Spread sugar, coconut and egg mixture over jam.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake(parentheses = larger cake)
directions: Grease sides and bottom of spring-form pan and sprinkle with plain graham cracker crumbs. Make a paste with the remainder of crumbs and margarine. Line bottom of pan with 1/2 of mixture.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
In small bowl, beat bananas until smooth.

In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs until light and fluffy. Beat in vanilla and bananas. Add flour mixture; beat just until blended. Add water until blended. Stir in chopped dates.
Put
in greased loaf pan. Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken lo mein(canton style - china)
directions: Combine chicken, 1 teaspoon salt, soy sauce, sugar, cooking wine and cornstarch.
Stir in 2 teaspoons oil.
Boil noodles for 2 minutes.
Drain.
Heat wok or pan on high.
Add 2 teaspoons oil; when some smoke comes out of the oil, put in the garlic, then the onion, carrots, peppers and 2 teaspoons salt.
Cook for about 1 minute, then add mushrooms.
Fry for a few seconds, then remove them.
Add more oil to the wok; add the ginger, white part of the scallions, then the chicken.
Fry, then add the green part of the scallions and the shrimp.
Fry them all for a while, then add the vegetables and cooked noodles.
Stir them for a while; add the oyster sauce and stir again for a few seconds.
Serves four.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Place half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Refrigerate until set. Spread sour cream over jello.
Pour remaining jello mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes. Salt and pepper to taste. Dredge in flour and brown in oil. Remove from oil. Brown onion and paprika. Add other ingredients and cook until meat is tender. Stir sour cream into broth when meat and vegetables are done.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread according to instructions.
Press bread dough onto a greased cookie sheet until it's approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Top with pizza sauce, keeping sauce about 1 inch away from edges.
Top with cheese, pepperoni, peppers and mushrooms.
Fold into thirds, pinch the ends and fold them under.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 400°. Put the ground beef, onions and celery. Brown, stirring frequently. Spoon off fat. Combine the green pepper, chili sauce, catsup, water, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, dry mustard, paprika and chili powder, mixing well. Pour over meat. Cover frying pan; turn to 220°. Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: deviled ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls.
Chill until firm; roll in shelled sunflower seeds.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Toast pecan halves in 325° oven until golden brown.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in sugar and salt.
Fold in nuts.
Melt margarine on large cookie sheet.
Spread nut mixture over margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: shrimp or crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper, until onions are clear.
Add soups and tomatoes.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add shrimp and crawfish tails, simmer for 15 minutes more.
Serve over rice.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together, then put in 2 pie crusts. Bake at 350° until done.

title: standing rib roast
directions: Preheat oven to 550°.
Place roast beef fat side up in a shallow roasting pan.
Sprinkle with garlic powder or thyme, salt and pepper.
Place in oven and immediately reduce heat to 350°. Roast 18 to 20 minutes per pound for a medium-rare roast.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Cut off tips of the asparagus; drop in boiling water for 30 seconds and drain.
Set aside.
Cut remaining stalks into 1/2-inch lengths.
Melt half of the butter and saute the stalks and the shallots for 5 minutes.
Set aside.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Cook beef, sausage, onion, green pepper and celery together until redness is gone from meat, then add all ingredients together except the cheese.
Pour in an 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, then sprinkle the grated cheese on top and return to the oven until cheese melts.

title: hamburger potato cheese pie
directions: Mix meat, salt, pepper, onion, bread crumbs (soaked in milk) and egg.
Spread in a 9-inch pie pan or casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Top with potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: chocolate berry trifle
directions: Pour milk into large mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix, beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Gently stir in 1 cup whipped topping.
Spread strawberry spread evenly over half the cake slices.
Top
with remaining cake slices; cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place half of the cake cubes in a large serving bowl; cover with half of combined fruit.
Top with 1 cup whipped topping and half of topping/pudding mixture.
Layer with remaining cake cubes, fruit, whipped topping and pudding/topping mixture. Garnish, if desired.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: Heat the first 3 ingredients until sugar dissolves; cool.
Add milk and whipped cream.
Pour in ice cream freezer and turn until creamed.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll in balls in cinnamon sugar on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool pasta.
Add sliced cucumbers, wedged tomatoes, sliced celery, any optional items as desired, Italian dressing and cheese.
Mix and refrigerate a few hours or overnight.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Combine cake
mix,
oil, 7-Up and 4 eggs.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: beef zucchini skillet(yields 4 servings)
directions: In mixing bowl, combine beef, onion, egg, oregano, salt and pepper until blended; shape into 20 balls, about 2-inches in diameter.
Heat butter in large skillet and brown meat balls in butter. Place zucchini on top of meat balls; cover and simmer until zucchini is tender, about 30 minutes.
Place meat balls and zucchini on warmed platter.
Reserve 1/4 cup meat drippings; stir in flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir until melted; pour some of sauce on meat balls and zucchini.
Serve the remaining portion in a bowl.
Contains approximately 460 calories.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix milk and egg.
Stir in corn.
Drop in deep hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Drain. Serve hot.

title: spinach dip
directions: Steam Spinach.
Add all the ingredients together.
Mix well. Cut out circle in middle of bread.
Pour dip in center of bread. Cut up the middle of loaf in chunks, use for dipping.

title: meatball stew
directions: Mix ground beef with salt, pepper, egg, minced onion and bread crumbs.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Brown in hot oil. Remove balls from skillet.
Pour off all fat, except for 3 tablespoons.
Blend in flour.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring to boil, simmer over low heat for 10 minutes, adding more water, if necessary.
Add to meatballs in a 2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 1 hour, until vegetables are tender.
Serves 6.

title: 30 minute chili
directions: Brown meat and drain grease.
Add chopped onion and cook until limp.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: thomasville burger
directions: Mix all ingredients real well.
Form into burgers.
Use to serve a large group or freeze.
Make size of your choice.

title: wheat bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine hot tap water with 7 cups whole wheat flour. Mix until well blended.
Add salt and honey or sugar.
Mix until well blended.
Add 1 cup flour, then yeast mixture and blend thoroughly.
Add 3 or 4 cups flour and knead dough until it begins to clean sides of the bowl.
Oil hands.
Separate dough into sizes to suit your pans.
Oil top; cover with damp cloth.
Let rise 1/3 in bulk (approximately 35 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: never fail no-beat popovers
directions: Break eggs into bowl; add milk, flour and salt.
Mix well with spoon, disregarding lumps.
Fill well-greased Pyrex custard cups 3/4 full.
Place in a cold oven.
Set control at 450° and turn on heat.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Don't dare peek!
After the 30 minutes baking time, open oven and pop into a bread basket.
Serve with tons of butter.
Then sit back and try not to look smug! Yields 8 popovers.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box.
Cool.
Split layers.
Fold dry icing mix into Cool Whip.
Spread between all layers.
Spread chocolate icing on top and sides of cake.
Top with crushed Heath Bars.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Cut 15 marshmallows into fourths and put on a tray in the freezer.
In a large glass bowl, cut the margarine into the chocolate chips.
Set aside.

title: cucumber vinaigrette
directions: Mix cucumbers and scallions; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Combine first mixture with second mixture.
Sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Chill.

title: butterscotch sauce for ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat to a boil while stirring.
Bring to boil to 220° on candy thermometer or boil 3 minutes.
Serve over ice cream, cream puffs, etc.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli separately.
Mix 1/4 Velveeta cheese and soup with rice and broccoli.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetables and pasta with cheese
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Add broccoli, cauliflower and carrots for last 5 minutes of cooking time. Drain.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil, add tomato sauce, simmer for at least 20 minutes or longer.
Slice artichoke hearts, dip in flour, then egg; fry until golden brown in a little oil.
Layer sauce, artichoke hearts and bread crumbs, end with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie pan 2/3 full of peeled and sliced apples.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Combine last 6 ingredients in a small bowl and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Can be frozen.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix well and pour into a 4 x 7-inch loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy southern-style lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain grease.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in all other ingredients except the lasagna noodles and the cheese.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
While sauce is cooking, cook lasagna.
Drain.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Cook meat and onions together. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 2 hours. Serve topped with sour cream, chopped green onions and tortilla chips.

title: crunchy rhubarb cake
directions: Blend 1 1/2 cups sugar and remaining ingredients except cinnamon and rhubarb.
Fold in rhubarb and put in 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon for top; sprinkle on.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: smish
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Drain spinach and mushrooms; stir into beef.
Heat all until warm.
Beat in one egg. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese to melt before eating.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix chicken, soups and Ro-Tel to a boil. Preheat oven to 350°. When above mixture boils, remove from heat. Layer tortilla shells in bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish; add half of heated mixture, then cheese. Add a layer of tortilla on top of the cheese, then pour remaining mixture on and cover with cheese to taste. Bake for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients with hand-mixer.
Add drained shrimp; mix with spoon.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Sweet Dough:
Mix milk, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Crumble in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Stir in eggs and shortening.
Mix in flour first with spoon, then with hand until easy to handle. Knead; let rise in warm oven 60 minutes.
Punch down; let rise second time.
Punch down; divide dough in half.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Add sugar, eggs and oil and mix.
Then add cocoa and food coloring.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk and 1/2 flour.
Mix well before adding the remaining flour and milk.
Mix together the other ingredients.
Pour into 3 sprayed cake pans and bake at 350° until done.

title: hamburger beans
directions: Scramble hamburger and onion.
Add beans, syrup, ketchup, mustard, salt and pepper (to taste).
Simmer in skillet until hot, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put bread and milk together in bowl.
Let set until bread is soaked.
May need a little more milk, then add egg, soups and spices.
Mix well, then add ground beef.
Form in small roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add vanilla, sugar and oil.
Stir in zucchini. In a small bowl, sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Add nuts and stir into dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake for 60 minutes at 325°.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into well greased iron skillet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Spread crushed cookies on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save a few crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Mix together the Cool Whip, cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter.
In a separate bowl, mix together the pudding mix and milk.
Combine both mixtures and pour over top of crumbs.
Sprinkle rest of cookie crumbs on top and refrigerate.

title: "some like it hot" meat loaf
directions: When mixed well, pick up and toss into bowl a few times to pack mixture together.
Form into loaf shape in cast-iron skillet which has been sprayed with cooking spray (Pam) and smear remaining tomato sauce/Tabasco over top of meat loaf.
(I use a skillet so I can make gravy in the same pan after the meat loaf is done.)
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Look at it now and then and if the pan is dry, add a little water.
Remove loaf from skillet and allow to cool long enough to make gravy before cutting.
Mix a little flour into drippings; add milk, stirring constantly, until desired thickness for gravy.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil sugar, corn syrup and water together until it spins a thread (240°), or until it forms a firm ball when dropped in cold water.
Beat egg white until stiff and pour syrup mixture slowly into egg white.
Beat rapidly until all syrup mixture is added to egg white.
Fold in nuts, raisins and coconut.
Beat constantly until mixture stands alone.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed or oiled paper.
Serve when cold.
(I use a wooden spoon to beat.)

title: colonial corn bread
directions: Bake corn bread in an iron skillet at 450° until brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until well done.
Drain excess grease.
Put ground beef in a deep bread pan.
Arrange Tater Tots on top of ground beef.
Mix mushroom and chicken soup together.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle bacon bits over top.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: saturday morning t. v. breakfast
directions: Tear tortillas into 3 or 4 pieces (like chips); brown gently until crispy in a small amount of oil.
Scramble eggs in a bowl; pour over the top of the tortillas.
Stir until cooked.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Top with cooked meat and onions.
Happy munchin' ... like morning nachos!

title: smothered beef
directions: Melt shortening (or use water) to brown meat.
Add garlic, tomato sauce, water, salt, sugar, mustard, pepper and bay leaves. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add onions and cook 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: milky way cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Melt 12 ounces of candy bars with 1 stick butter or 1/2 cup oil; stir until all smooth.
Pour onto cake batter.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour into any cake pan that you desire.
Melt 16 ounces of candy bars as before.
While still warm, spread evenly over cake.
Let stand until cool.

title: coconut crisp delight
directions: Melt butter. Mix the flour, coconut, almonds and brown sugar. Press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes until golden brown. Set aside and cool in pan baked in.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.

title: shrimp and pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; cool.
Combine shrimp, cooled pasta, chopped eggs, celery, onion and sweet pickle relish in a large bowl; toss well.
Pour French dressing, salt and pepper over mixture and toss.
Chill until served.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all
the ingredients and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion, sugar, salt and pepper in oleo.
Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs, together and pour into greased dish and cover top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook beef, onion and bacon in skillet until meat and onion are tender.
Drain fat.
Stir with remaining ingredients into 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or cook on top of stove.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch, salt and lemon rind.
Add hot water gradually, blending well.
Cook in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Beat egg yolks with lemon juice.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return to saucepan gradually, stirring constantly.
Add butter and cook for 2 minutes longer.
Cool.
Pour filling into pie shell.

title: fruit punch(serves 65)
directions: Pick the grapes.
Clean them.
Put in boiler.
Put water half way up on grapes.
Turn on high.
Wait until boils.
Turn to medium.
Wait until boils.
Turn to low.
Cook until skins split. Take them out and tie to spigot.
This recipe has never been tested.

title: preston county buckwheat cakes
directions: Serve with fried potatoes, whole hot sausage, maple syrup and butter.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Sift
flour,
salt
and
spices.
Add nuts and raisins. Cream shortening	and
sugar.
Add eggs.	Stir baking soda in applesauce;
add
to
the first mixture.
Combine ingredients. Drop
by
spoonful, 3 inches apart, onto greased baking sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix all together with a small jar of Cheez Whiz.
Bake in large casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add oats, egg, milk and oil.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well and pour into a 9-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce. Serves 9.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix together.
Season to taste.
Shape into approximately 6 patties.
Dip in flour.
Brown slowly in butter, five minutes each side.

title: oven brisket
directions: Mix sauces and pour in roasting pan.
Generously cover both sides of brisket with seasonings.
Lay, fat side up, in sauce. Cover and bake at 275° for 6 to 8 hours.
Can cook it longer or overnight.

title: orange lollypops
directions: You will need
24 ice cream bar sticks.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Place 1 vanilla wafer in cupcake paper.
Mix sugar, cream cheese, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into cupcake papers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheets to cool on wire rack.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix milk, Cool Whip and coloring.
Fold in filling, nuts and pineapple.
Pour in casserole dish. Chill. This is pretty for the holidays.

title: *russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
For each cup of hot water, use approximately 1 level tablespoon or to taste.
For pot, use ingredients listed and add to 10- cups of hot water; heat.
Serves 10 cups.

title: cauliflower goldenrod
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Combine milk and water in pan and bring to boil.
Add cauliflower, cover and cook 10 minutes. Drain.
Toss cauliflower and 2 tablespoons butter until coated. Transfer to serving dish.

title: barbecue spareribs(this is a microwave recipe for tender cooker)
directions: Place ribs, onions and garlic in tender cooker.
Combine sauce and water together and pour over ribs.
Cover and add red pressure regulator weight.
Microwave on High for 20 minutes.
Allow pressure indicating stem to drop.
Remove red pressure regulator weight and uncover.
Makes four servings.
A 400 to 500 watt oven requires extended time of approximately 5 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: **Drain and whirl in food processor.

title: cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan (oblong).
Put dry ingredients into bowl. Add eggs and oil.
Mix. Add orange juice and vanilla. Mix again. Batter will be thick.
Spread with a spoon.
Pour half the batter into pan. Add cherries and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Pour remaining batter.
Spread with spoon and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°. Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 40 minutes longer.

title: chocolate chip mint torte
directions: In medium bowl, combine cookie crumbs and margarine.
Reserve 1/4 cup crumbs.
Press remaining crumbs in bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Freeze 1 hour.
Place ice cream in a large bowl.
Gently fold in whipped cream.
Spoon mixture into crust lined pan.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Cover. Freeze 5 hours or overnight.
Makes 10 servings.

title: marie's 4th of july jubilee trifle
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Cut pound cake into 1-inch cubes. Spread a thin layer of pudding on the bottom of bowl and begin layering as follows:
cake cubes, pudding, blueberry filling, pudding, cake, pudding, cherry pie filling (or strawberry) and top with Cool Whip.
Decorate top with remaining blueberry and cherry pie filling if desired.
It looks very festive.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Melt together oleo, oil, cocoa and water.
Pour this mixture into the sugar mixture.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix these all together well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a jelly-roll cake pan.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine and cook all ingredients together for 45 minutes (simmer).

title: cheese ball
directions: Let ingredients stand at room temperature.
Blend together cream cheese, salt, dip and butter until blended.
Set in refrigerator until firm.
Roll into balls and roll in chopped nuts.

title: sopa de codito
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Add oil, then add macaroni and cook for 15 minutes.
Rinse in cold water; set aside.
Using the same pan, saute garlic and onion in small amount of oil.
When onion starts to brown, add tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Add macaroni and let it simmer over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes. Add cheese and cover for 5 minutes more.
Ready to serve.

title: raspberry-almond coffeecake(low-fat)
directions: Combine raspberries and brown sugar in a bowl.
Toss well and set aside.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Combine yogurt and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon two-thirds of batter into an 8-inch round cake pan, coated with cooking spray, and spread evenly.
Top with raspberry mixture.
Spoon remaining batter over raspberry mixture; top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar, milk and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla; stir well.
Drizzle over cake.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Yield:
8 servings.
Serving size:
1 wedge. Calories:
Fat grams:

title: ritz peanut butter cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers, set aside.
Melt almond bars in microwave oven (in microwave dish) for 1 minute; stir mixture well.
Continue microwaving for 15 minute intervals; stirring well after each interval until smooth consistency.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Place chuck roast in roasting pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over roast; cover pan.
Bake in 325° oven about 3 hours or until fork-tender.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Mix next 3 ingredients, then add to flour mixture.
Mold into 4 balls and chill for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 double pie crusts.

title: texas stew
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2 inch cubes; season with flour.
Heat olive oil in deep iron skillet or Dutch oven.
Brown meat slowly; add other ingredients.
Cover tightly, turn meat often and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: annie wingate's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add salt, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and confectioners sugar until crumbly.
Place in pie shell.
Save 2 tablespoons for topping.
Make up vanilla pudding mix and place on top of peanut butter mixture.
After pudding cools, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle the 2 tablespoons of topping over pie.

title: virginia sweet potato pie
directions: Blend butter, salt and sugar.
Add egg yolks, lemon juice, spices, potato pulp and hot milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Place in pie shell.
Bake in a hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes, then in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 40 minutes, until pie is firm in center.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Saute garlic and yellow and green onions in olive oil until tender; remove and set aside.
Pound chicken breasts flat.
Mix salt and pepper with flour in flat dish.
Cover chicken with flour.
Lightly brown the chicken in butter 2 to 3 minutes per side.
Add the onions and garlic.
Over high heat, add sherry, lemon juice and capers.
Mixture should thicken into nice gravy for over chicken.
If too thick, may thin with chicken stock. Garnish with chopped parsley and lemon slice.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break cake into pieces in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Add 2 cups of milk to pudding. Mix as directed. Mix well and pour over cake. Add jello to boiling water.
Stir until dissolved. Add strawberries and stir. Pour over cake and pudding mixture. Chill until set. Yields 15 servings.

title: burrito roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, taco seasoning and green onions. Lay out burritos on wax paper, then spread mixture evenly on all burritos within 1/8-inch of edge. Roll burritos tight and put in a freezer bag. Refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight. Slice burritos into small pieces. Serve cold with salsa on the side.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; set aside.
Saute onion in drippings. Drain off drippings.
Add remaining ingredients and crumbled bacon. Cook for 20 to 30 minutes on low.

title: no crust cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients about 2 minutes until light and fluffy.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown around the edges.
Remove from oven and cool.
Top with desired topping.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Saute onion and parsley in oil; add garlic powder.
Drain 2 cans clams; leave 2 with liquid.
Mix in with onion.
Slowly add 1 cup (more or less) of seasoned bread crumbs to reach desired consistency.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on top and bake 1/2 hour in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
