title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix eggs, oil and berries with mixer. Combine together. Add nuts and mix until just moistened.
Bake in greased floured pans or four 1 pound cans at 350° for 1 hour, less time for small loaves.

title: fruited cheese log
directions: Spread almonds in shallow pan.
Toast at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
Combine dates, raisins, apricots and sherry, tossing well to combine; set aside.
Blend cream cheese, Muenster cheese, mustard and salt; mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup almonds and sherry-fruit mixture.
Turn out onto foil.
Shape into a log; cover and chill until firm.
Roll in remaining almonds and parsley before serving.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes 1 (8-inch) log.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into prepared shell. Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Beat until smooth.
Add bananas and milk.
Add flour mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
This bread is even better the next day.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all together well with mixer.
Add nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: ham and pineapple loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients with the exception of the pineapple.
Form into patties; place in baking dish, alternating meat patties and pineapple slices.

title: french toast
directions: In shallow bowl or nonmetal pan, whisk together eggs, milk, cinnamon, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Cut bread into 1-inch slices on the diagonal to make larger slices.
Soak bread in egg mixture until all slices are evenly coated.

title: pecan and raisin pie
directions: Put raisins in water and boil 2 to 3 minutes; drain.
Mix all ingredients together with raisins.
Put mixture in already made pie crust and bake until brown at 350°.

title: sunny scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat potatoes with combined flour and seasonings.
Place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Heat Velveeta and milk over low heat.
Add green pepper, onion and pimiento. Pour Velveeta sauce over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until potatoes are done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook the ingredients about 20 or 25 minutes in broth.
Add cornbread, some slices of loaf bread and 4 eggs, which have been beaten, then set in refrigerator overnight.

title: cinnamon candy salad
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water into Jell-O and candy red hots. Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup cold water.
When candy is melted and gelatin is dissolved, mix together.
Add 2 cups applesauce.
Mold and chill.

title: potica cake
directions: Melt margarine with milk and cool. Mix yeast, sugar and water. Let stand.
Add 3 cups flour, salt and 5 tablespoons sugar to liquids.
Beat well and refrigerate overnight.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and add taco mix.
Layer lettuce, meat, tomatoes, onion, beans and cheese; chill.
When ready to serve, add crushed chips and dressing if you want.

title: old fashioned peach cookies
directions: In blender, blend pie filling until smooth.
In large mixing bowl, combine pie filling, dry cake mix and eggs.
Blend well; stir in nuts.
Drop from tablespoon on greased baking sheet.
If desired, sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Beat egg; stir in buttermilk, brown sugar and shortening.
Mix in remaining ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: kelli's scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add flour.
It will be stiff and crumbly, but carry on.
Press into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes, then cut in squares.

title: polynesian luau
directions: Stew chicken and save juice for gravy.
Bone chicken into bite size pieces.
To the broth of the chicken, add one can creamed mushroom and one can golden mushroom soup.
Rinse cans out with a little water.
Add the chicken and simmer for about an hour.
Add salt to taste.

title: 5 flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beaten well.
Combine flour and baking powder to mixture. Add milk.
Put in 10-inch tube pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Leave in pan for 10 minutes after baking.
(Add flavorings to mix with milk.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Add other ingredients, shape into balls or logs and roll in chopped nuts.
This will make 2 fairly large balls.
If processor is used, process nuts, then onoin, then cheese.
This way you won't have to wash processor until finished.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix all 5 cans together.
Cover top with crushed potato chips or crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients
and divide among the 3 cans.
Bake at 350° for 1
hour.
Loosen
in
can with long knife after it has cooled 15
minutes.
Finish
cooling on rack.
Good served with cream cheese.
Also good to freeze.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: *Use strawberries, cherries or other fruit.
A 10 ounce package of frozen fruit or a
1 pound
can of fruit will be sufficient.

title: cranberry ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a large bowl; add cranberry sauce and next 3 ingredients, stirring until blended. Chill mixture to the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in fruit.
Pour mixture into a lightly oiled 6-cup ring mold; cover and chill until firm.
Makes 10 to 11 servings.

title: lacy oat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the sugar and butter or margarine until fluffy.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes. Let cookies stand for 3 minutes before removing with a wide spatula.
Makes about 30 thin, lacy cookies.

title: crispy oven baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Process cornflakes, cheese and spices in blender or processor.
Dip potatoes in butter, then cornflake mixture.
Place on a well-greased baking sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar, karo and water to 230 degrees.
Add peanuts and stir constantly to 320 degrees or until peanuts are golden brown. Remove from heat and add soda, salt and butter.
Place on 2 greased cookie sheets.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: steak
directions: Take meat and rinse in cold water.
Sprinkle a desired amount of pepper and salt on both sides.
Pour A.1. sauce on meat.
With back of a spoon, spread around on both sides of meat.
In a heated pan, put meat in and cook until both sides are fairly brown. Enjoy.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer on a flat plate:
bean dip (spread with a knife to cover plate).
Mix mayo, sour cream, taco mix and chili powder.
Spread over bean dip.
Top with green pepper, tomato and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: betty's oven barbecued chicken
directions: Place 6 to 8 chicken pieces in foil lined 9 x 12-inch pan. Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and heat to boiling point. Pour heated sauce over chicken pieces.
Seal foil over chicken. Place in 300° oven and bake for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: macaroni and tomato casserole
directions: Boil celery, bell pepper, tomatoes and onion 20 minutes. Boil macaroni 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add the butter to hot macaroni. Add and mix well all other ingredients except 1/2 of the cheese. Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: duck casserole
directions: Boil duck until tender.
Steam celery, onion and bell pepper in bacon grease.
Pour Ro-Tel in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour onion, celery and peppers on top.
Add boiled duck (deboned and cut in small pieces).
Add 1 box Uncle Ben's wild rice, sprinkling the seasoning over it.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup to the 2 cups of broth and beat before adding to the dish.
Cover with aluminum foil and cook approximately 35 minutes at 350°.
Be sure to cover dish or it will be dry.

title: baked beans
directions: Put bacon in 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Cool and skim off fat.
Add brown sugar to beans and mix well.
Bake at 350° for an hour or more.

title: funnel bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Cook in hot oil (400°), turning once.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy biscuits
directions: With a wooden spoon, mix ingredients.
Dough will be sticky. Use finger and spoon to fill small muffin tins about half full. Bake at 400° about 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Yields 24 biscuits.
Large muffin tins will not work with this recipe.

title: stuffed mushrooms caesar
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove and finely chop stems.
In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Fill each mushroom with mixture.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Add water to barely cover bottom.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: (This is good with canned peaches as well as fruit cocktail.) Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together and pour into baking dish.
DO NOT STIR.
Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Crust will rise to the top.

title: salsa
directions: Combine and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; let simmer for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate until use.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; bake at 350° for 40 minutes. cool.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cook vegetables in microwave; mix in other ingredients and cook until cheese bubbles.
Cook at 350°.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a jar and refrigerate. Will keep for a week.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs and apples.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed sugar mixture. Stir in chopped pecans and blend well.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pan and sprinkle with 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham loaf
directions: After 45 minutes baste with soup.

title: low-fat cream of tomato soup
directions: In blender container, place tomatoes and puree.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir with a wire whisk about 3 minutes or until sour cream is liquified.
Place mixture in saucepan over low heat stirring often.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.
Calories 130; cholesterol 1 mg., fat 6 grams, sodium 796 mg.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a skillet, cook ground chuck, onion and garlic until meat is browned; drain.
Transfer mixture to an electric slow cooker. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: pear butter
directions: Cook sugar and pears 25 minutes from time of boiling.
Add pineapple and cook until thick.

title: tandy cake
directions: Bake on large cookie sheet (11 x 17-inch) for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
As soon as you take cake from oven, spread with peanut butter.
Refrigerate until cold.
Melt an 8 ounce milk chocolate bar and spread over cake.

title: simply wonderfuls
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Remove from heat and cool slightly. Add sugar and stir until creamy. Add milk, nuts, coconut and raisins gradually and mix continually. Roll into 1-inch balls. If too dry, add more butter; if too wet, add more powdered sugar. Roll balls in powdered sugar.

title: angel kisses
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Add almond extract and vanilla; mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto aluminum foil lined cookie sheets.
(The kisses do not spread.)
Place in a 350° oven; immediately turn off oven. Let stand 8 to 10 minutes or overnight.
Do not open oven door. Store in airtight containers ready for serving or gift giving.

title: turtle candy
directions: Melt caramels; add milk and stir until smooth.
Add pecans. Spoon onto greased cookie sheet; freeze for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Melt Hershey bars and paraffin; dip squares into chocolate.
Place on buttered cookie sheet to set.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in broth.
Save the broth.
Puree the broccoli. Melt margarine and make a paste with the flour.
Add to broth slowly, stirring constantly.
Add the half and half.
Add broccoli, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Stir and heat until very hot. Makes 4 quarts.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over margarine.
Sprinkle coconut over cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle chips over coconut, then sprinkle nuts over chips.
Pour condensed milk over nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan and cut into 1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch squares.
Cool 2 hours before serving.

title: jenay evans' blueberry  muffins
directions: Clean and rinse berries. Pat dry.
Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until well mixed.
Beat in eggs.

title: scrambled omelet
directions: In skillet, heat oil and saute onion and bell pepper. Add ham and heat.
Add beaten eggs; cook until eggs are half cooked.
Add grated cheese.
Cook to doneness as desired.

title: pizza burgers(makes 12)
directions: Brown beef and allow to cool.
In a large bowl, mix beef and all other ingredients, except muffins.
Spread mixture heavily on 1/2 an English muffin.
Top with other 1/2 of muffin.
Wrap individually in foil and freeze.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: randy's etouffee
directions: Chop onions, bell pepper and celery; put in blender.
Add 1 cup of water, 1/2 can of Ro-Tel and 1/2 hand of crawfish tails into blender (10 or 15 tails).
Blend these ingredients.
Pour blended ingredients into 4-quart pot with 1 block of butter and 1/2 cup of water.
Cover top of pot with McCormick Season-All (one layer thick).
Add 1/2 cap of liquid crab boil and 4 dashes of Tabasco.
Saute (cook on medium-high heat for 20 minutes).
Stir! Mix 1 cup of water with 3 tablespoons of flour and pour into mixture.
Cook for 5 minutes on medium-high heat (to thicken). Stir!
Then add crawfish tails and chopped onion tops to pot. Cook for 20 minutes on low heat.
Stir; don't let stick! When finished, cover and let stand for 15 minutes.
Then pour over cooked rice and enjoy!
Serves 4 humans or 2 animals.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Heat German chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk on low heat. Beat 2 tablespoons sugar into cream cheese, 1/3 cup milk and chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold into small Cool Whip. Blend until smooth.
Blend into graham cracker pie shell.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased loaf tins. (Makes 2 small loaves or 1 large loaf.)

title: caramel corn crunch
directions: Mix all but vanilla in heavy pan.
Bring to boil; cook to 290°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Pour over about 15 cups of popcorn.
It will be sticky at first, but stir well.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco, adding sugar gradually.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add to mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into tube pan that has been well-greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Place shallow pan of water on bottom of oven.

title: louisiana cornbread dressing
directions: Cook giblets until tender.
Cut all meat fine for dressing. Saute celery, shallots and onion in the butter until done but not brown; add seasonings, more or less than amounts suggested to suit individual taste.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine next seven ingredients, add to creamed mixture alternately with pumpkin, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in vanilla, raisins and pecans. Spoon into 4 greased and floured one pound coffee cans. Bake at 350° for one hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in cans 10 minutes, remove from cans and cool completely on wire racks. Yields: 4 loaves. Can also be baked in loaf pans.

title: pork barbecue sauce
directions: Mix altogether and spread over pork.

title: tuna-cashew casserole
directions: Start heating oven to 325°.
Set aside 1/2 cup Chinese noodles. In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine rest of noodles with soup, water, tuna (which has been broken up into medium size pieces), nuts, celery, onions and pepper.
Taste and add salt, if necessary. Sprinkle reserved noodles over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp and scallop casserole
directions: Coat shrimp with oil and spread in a baking dish.
Mix butter, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, A.1., lemon and garlic. Pour over shrimp.
Mix in scallops and top with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cocktail franks
directions: Mix cranberry sauce, brown sugar, mustard, lemon juice and salt.
Heat ingredients.
Add hot dogs and cook on medium-high heat until boils.
Simmer in fondue pot or crock-pot to serve.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Simmer chicken in unsalted water until done.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups broth. Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add this to the stuffing mix.
Divide this mixture.
Place half in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with chicken.
Place other half of stuffing mixture on top. Mix together both cans of soup and the reserved broth.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: deluxe shrimp casserole
directions: Place shrimp in a single layer in a large, well greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper to taste.
In a small skillet, heat the oil, add the mushrooms and saute until lightly browned; remove to large bowl and toss with flour.
Stir in the sour cream, melted butter and soy sauce, mix well.
Pour over shrimp, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven until heated through, about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: puppy chow
directions: Put chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo in a microwave-safe dish and microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Stir after 1 minute.
When melted, add vanilla.
Pour chocolate mix over Chex.
Mix well until cereal is all coated.
Put powdered sugar in a large Ziploc bag.
Add chocolate coated Chex and shake. Spread on wax paper until cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut boiled chicken breasts into pieces; place in casserole dish.
Mix together mushroom soup, chicken soup, sour cream and mushrooms; spread over chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Place on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: frozen fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients and ladle into paper cup lined muffin tins.
Freeze.

title: carrot croquettes
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Heat shortening in frypan until moderately hot.
Drop mixture by large spoonfuls into fat.
Fry slowly and turn with spatula to brown on other side.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: southern sweet potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes; add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Stir twice during baking.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients; let stand 30 minutes.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill before serving.

title: strawberry or blueberry delight
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 crumbs on buttered pan. Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs.
Beat well.
Spread on crumbs.
Next, spread berries on cream mixture.
Top with whipped cream.
Sprinkle nuts and the remaining crushed wafers on the whipped cream.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine corn and eggs. Add flour which has been sifted with remaining ingredients. Drop corn mixture from tablespoon into 1 inch of melted shortening. Brown until golden on both sides, turning once.

title: pecan pie(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Cream butter to soften. Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy. Add sugar and salt. Beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Stir in pecans. Pour in pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick and sugar.
Add sour cream, soda and egg.
Knead a little using Bisquick on board.
Roll 1/2-inch thick; cut and bake in dripper pan with biscuits touching.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, then flour, cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and apples.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes until done.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Fit crescent rolls into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish or pizza pan, covering bottom and sides.
Press edges to seal.
Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Layer sausage and cheese in prepared pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well. Pour over layers.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: easy pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one bowl.
Add the melted shortening in last.
Heat griddle, then pour mixture onto griddle. When mix bubbles up, flip with spatula.
When pancakes become a golden brown, remove and top with your favorite syrup.
Enjoy.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: In large saucepan, over low heat, melt butter and chocolate, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. Stir in flour, sugar, walnuts, baking powder, salt and eggs; mix well.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour for easier handling.
Heat oven to 300°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll each into 10x sugar, coating heavily.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 13 to 18 minutes, or until set.
Remove from cookie sheets immediately.
Cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and put in 8 x 8-inch shallow baking pan. Crush potato chips, enough to cover, about 2 cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve right from baking pan.

title: cranberry chappaqua crunch cookies
directions: Mix in order of listing.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix well and bake in four layers at 375° for about 25 minutes. Let cool.

title: basic sweet dough
directions: This may be made into rolls, sticky buns or rolled buns.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Shred cheese and mix all ingredients. Form into 1-inch balls. Bake 15 minutes on ungreased baking sheet until golden brown. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In large bowl, soak bread crumbs for 10 minutes. Melt 1 Tbsp. butter in large skillet over medium heat. Saute onion until soft. Stir onion into bread crumbs. Add beef, pork, egg, parsley, salt and spices. Beat at high speed with electric mixer until mixture is fluffy. Use 2 cold, wet teaspoons to shape mixture into tiny meatballs. Melt 2 Tbsp. butter in same skillet. Brown meatballs, turning to brown all sides evenly. Drain on paper towels. Stir flour into drippings in skillet. Add meatballs to sauce. Simmer 15 minutes. Makes 48 meatballs.

title: "glebus globus"
directions: Bring potatoes and onions to a boil.
Drain. Put in buttered dish or pan the potatoes as the first layer, then the onions as the second layer.
Add 1 layer of hamburger patties. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar and corn syrup.
Blend in eggs and vanilla extract.
Add pecans. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until well done.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage in frying pan.
Add butter and flour.
Mix well.
Add milk to thicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
This is great served over homemade biscuits.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Sweeten berries with the 1/4 cup sugar.
Place in bottom of 1-quart buttered casserole.
Mix all remaining ingredients and spoon over blueberries and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla yogurt ice cream.
Peaches may also be used instead of blueberries.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: buckeyes
directions: Combine Rice Krispies, margarine, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Form into balls.

title: meltaway cheese rounds(appetizers)
directions: Cream butter in food processor or mixer until light and fluffy. Add cheese, flour, salt and paprika or poppy seed.
Form to a dough.
Chill dough for about 2 hours.
Shape dough into small even balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with some extra paprika or poppy seed, if desired.
Bake balls at 400° for about 10 minutes or until just baked through.
The rounds should never get browned.
Cool on the cookie sheet.
Remove carefully.
Store in airtight containers until ready to serve.
When serving, reheat for a few minutes at 400° until slightly warm.

title: rich waffles
directions: Stir together and bake in waffle iron until brown.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Let cool and add pineapple and pie filling. Let partially set. Add sour cream (swirl it into mixture).
Chill until completely firm. Can top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine salt and pepper with flour; pound into steak.
Heat oil; brown steak well on both sides.
Reduce heat; add onions. When just wilted, add liquids and seasonings.
Cover; simmer for 2 hours, or until steak is tender, turning once or twice.
Serve with pan sauce.

title: corn light bread
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together; add buttermilk and oil. Bake in well-greased loaf
pan
with double thickness of oiled paper at bottom for about
hour
at
or
until nicely brown.
Let stand a while to sweat.

title: twenty four hour salad
directions: Layer: lettuce, eggs, peas, cheese, green onion and Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle bacon bits over the top.
Refrigerate overnight. Next day, stir before serving.

title: orange baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow pan, meat side up.
Sprinkle onions, rosemary, paprika and pepper over chicken.
Blend flour with orange juice and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven until done, about 1 hour.
Baste often with juice. Makes 5 servings.
Contains 185 calories per serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Break up chicken and place in baking dish.
Mix soups and sour cream; pour 1 1/2 cups of broth over top and bake 40 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: all natural cough syrup(good for sore throat)
directions: Mix all together.
Shake well.
Take one swallow at night.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick; blend sugar and eggs.
Continue blending as oil and buttermilk are added.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Mix dry ingredients and sift.
Blend in dry mixture; add vanilla.
Divide batter equally into 3 greased and lightly floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot water.
Add strawberries and crushed pineapple.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into square Pyrex dish to congeal.
Cream sugar, mayonnaise and cream cheese together.
(You may use a little milk if necessary.)
Spread this mixture over the congealed Jello.
Chill.
Add remaining Jello mixture and congeal. To serve, cut into squares.
It's pretty and good topped with a tablespoon of sour cream and a whole strawberry.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: Mix soup, 1/2 can of water and rice in bowl (may need more water). Layer rice mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Bury chicken breasts in rice mixture. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until rice is fluffy and chicken is tender.

title: bacon-stuffed flounder rolls
directions: Grease eight 2 1/2-inch muffin pans.
Set aside.
Cook bacon until crisp and drain.
Reserve drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Add melted oleo to drippings to make 1/4 cup.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions using 1/4 cup drippings.
Stir in bacon, onion, and parsley.
Wrap 1 fish fillet inside each muffin cup and press against sides.
Spoon 1/2 cup of stuffing into center of each roll.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Prepare and serve with Bearnaise sauce.

title: minted salad with cucumbers
directions: Peel, seed and chop cucumbers.
Sprinkle with salt and allow to drain for half an hour.
Line a sieve with a coffee filter.
Pour yogurt in and allow to drain for half an hour.
In a glass or pottery serving bowl, combine yogurt with remaining ingredients. Stir in cucumber.
Cover and refrigerate if not served at once. Yield:
8 servings.
Carbohydrate 6 g, protein 3 g, fat 2 g, calories 52.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix with stuffing.
Use half to line bottom of baking dish.
Mix other ingredients with salt and pepper.
Pour over stuffing mix, then top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven until casserole is done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown hamburger, pork and onions.
Put in tomato soup and simmer 30 minutes.
Add diced cream cheese. Cook noodles.
Alternate hamburger mixture with noodles and grated cheese in a large casserole dish.
Cover top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake for 20 minutes or until brown.
Serves 8.

title: italian garden salad
directions: Cut vegetables into bite sized pieces and add dressing.
Let marinate overnight and serve.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine carrots, pineapple and raisins.
Combine sugar, mayonnaise and yogurt, blending well.
Pour over carrot mixture and toss.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: black and white cookies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl beat butter, both sugars and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until fluffy.
Beat in eggs until well blended.
On low speed, gradually mix in dry ingredients, just until well blended.
With a wooden spoon, stir in chips.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Bake white cake as directed on box.
Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 2 cups cold water.
Make holes in cake with large fork.
Pour jello over cake.
Set in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: chinese salad
directions: Recipe has three steps.
Make each separately and then mix all together 20 minutes before serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: Mix
ingredients
and pour in 2 quart casserole.
Cover casserole
and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Good!

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Melt oleo; mix with 1/4 cup sugar and graham cracker crumbs. Pat into pie pan.
Chill.
Soften cream cheese and mix with 1/2 cup sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Spoon over graham cracker crust. Chill.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: sesame milk
directions: Soften
dates
by
simmering
in
1/2 cup water.
Grind seeds until fine.
Blend ingredients until smooth with 2 cups water. Put
into container and add remaining 1 1/2 cups water (use
to rinse blender).
Stir well.
Chill.
(Toasting seeds enhances the flavor.) Makes 4 cups.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Add enough water to make a gallon or 5 quarts.
Freeze for approximately 10 hours or until slushy.
Stir and serve.

title: squash puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful in deep fat until browned.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Add 1 teaspoon of sugar to yeast mixture.
Cool milk to warm and add to yeast.
Also add shortening, 3/4 cup sugar, salt and eggs. Beat well.
Add flour to make soft dough.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Knead.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn ball over to grease top side and cover.
Store in refrigerator.
Shape rolls 2 to 3 hours before baking.
Let rise. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Keeps in refrigerator about a week.

title: pumpkin dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat butter and sugar until fluffy; add oats and flour and mix well.
Spread evenly into pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Bake an additional 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely.
Chill and cut into 2-inch squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: cheese delight
directions: Mix eggs, tomato sauce, milk and seasonings.
Arrange alternate layers of bread, cheese and sauce in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Place in pan of hot water.
Bake in a slow 325° oven for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate coca-cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Combine Coca-Cola and butter in saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir to blend.
Mix in buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows (batter will be thin).
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Spread with warm frosting.

title: apple cranberry streusel custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and cinnamon.
Add eggs, water and fruit; mix well. Pour into pie shell.
In medium bowl, combine sugar and flour. Cut in butter until crumbly; add nuts.
Sprinkle over pie.
Place on lowest shelf of oven.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 375°.
Continue baking 30 to 40 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: french vanilla fluff
directions: Melt butter and mix with crackers.
Add nuts.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
In separate bowl, mix ice cream, pudding and milk. Mix for 5 to 7 minutes.
Put on top of crumbs and freeze at least 1 hour.
Before serving, cover with whipped topping and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and salt.
Let stand 3 hours in crushed ice. Drain; put in large pot.
Pour in mixture of other ingredients. Heat to boiling point, but do not boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: marinated fruit
directions: If you use peaches, immerse in boiling water for 2 minutes. Peel skin and cut peaches in half.
Remove stone.
Place in jar with strawberries.
Add a little sugar, if desired.
Add 4 to 6 ounces Grand Marnier and keep in fridge.
This can be prepared the day before.
Serve in large wine glasses (place over ice cream if desired).
Top with whipped cream and serve.

title: taco scrambler
directions: Saute green onions until tender.
Beat together eggs, milk, tomato, green chilies and salt.
Add egg mixture to onion.
Cook, stirring constantly, until eggs are firm.
Add in bacon or cubes of ham; stir.
Crisp taco shells by baking at 350° for 7 minutes. Spoon egg mixture into taco shell and top with taco sauce and heated cheese spread.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix the yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/2 cup warm water.
Let stand.
Mix 2 cups warm water, shortening, 2/3 cup sugar, eggs and salt.
Beat in 3 cups flour, then add yeast mixture.
Beat well, then add rest of the flour.
Put in covered bowl and let rise. Punch down and let rise again.
Shape into rolls and place in greased pan.
Let rise.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9-inch) round layer cake pans.
Line with waxed paper.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs for fudge-like brownies.
Bake for 20 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Cool.

title: red-skinned potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Drain.
Cut into thick slices.
Transfer to serving bowl.
Mix sour cream and yogurt together in small bowl.
Add dill and garlic.
Combine celery and scallions with potatoes.
Pour sour cream dressing over all and toss.
Garnish with fresh dill sprigs.
Serves 8.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain; combine onion, celery, green pepper, tuna and mayonnaise and mix well, then add salt and pepper to taste.

title: ma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix last 4 ingredients together and add to the rest.
Mix.
Form into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Wet a fork and press on cookie.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust or vanilla wafer crust.
Mix crushed vanilla wafers with melted butter; press into pie plate.
Sprinkle a few vanilla wafer crumbs on top of pie.
Refrigerate.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in double boiler. Heat over simmering water, stirring until melted.
Combine cake mix, remaining evaporated milk and soft butter.
Mix until mixture holds together.
Stir in nuts.
Press half of cake mix mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: vegetable gumbo
directions: Cook beef until it falls from the bone.
Reserve stock.
Mix all the stocks together.
Add vegetables and their juices, macaroni, and seasonings to the stock.
Simmer until very hot. Yields approximately 4 gallons.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cream margarine and sweetener.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Add applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients and mix in creamed mixture.
Fold in dates, nuts and apple.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Marinate brisket in mixture of next 5 ingredients in roaster overnight.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Bake, covered, for 5 hours. Cool in refrigerator.
Blend drippings, brown sugar, catsup and flour in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Slice brisket thinly across grain.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meatballs and beans
directions: Mix meat, eggs, bread crumbs, chili powder and onions together.
Form small meatballs and brown.
Add beans and simmer until warm.

title: whacky cake
directions: Sift together in 8 x 8-inch pan the flour, sugar, salt, soda and cocoa.
Make 3 holes in the dry mixture and add oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour water over this and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together turkey or chicken, celery, almonds, green pepper, pimento, onion, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Top with chips.
Bake in a 350° oven or microwave until heated through.

title: gourmet rice dressing
directions: Saute onion, celery, celery leaves, mushrooms and rice in butter until vegetables are tender and rice is golden.
Turn into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Stir in broth, salt and almonds.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Fluff with fork.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked caramel apples
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Melt butter and roll apples in mixture.
Place in a Pam-sprayed baking dish.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts and raisins over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy cream biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Add enough cream until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Roll to coat.
Knead lightly 10 times, sprinkling with flour if dough is sticky.
Roll or pat 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes about 12 biscuits.

title: easy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs and vegetable oil with cake mix and blend well.
(Nuts, raisins, chocolate chips or other ingredients of your choice may also be added.) Drop teaspoonfuls of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet, spacing each teaspoonful approximately 2 inches apart.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Slice tops
from tomatoes and save. Remove pulp; cut in small pieces
and
save.
Sprinkle
insides
of tomatoes with sugar and salt.
Heat 1/4 cup olive oil in large skillet.
Add onion and garlic
and
saute until onion is translucent.
Add meat and
cook until no longer red.
Add rice, seasonings and tomato
pulp. Simmer
10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Fill tomatoes 2/3 full
and place
them in a baking dish.
Put tops on tomatoes.
Drizzle remaining olive oil between tomatoes.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Bake at
350° about 40 to 45 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown chuck and onions; drain.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with mixed vegetables.
Add soup and milk.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix with milk in saucepan. Add peanut butter. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Cool cooked pudding 5 minutes, stirring twice. Pour into pie shell. Chill 3 hours.

title: cranberry-orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water, add spices.
Add cranberry sauce and orange rind.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in oranges and pour into 3 cup mold or individual molds.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Melt margarine.
Add to flour mixture; beat well.
Beat eggs with vanilla and add.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Lower oven to 325° and bake about 15 more minutes.
Pie will firm as it cools down.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion in a little olive oil in medium saucepan.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Small meatballs can be added or ground beef can be cooked with onion for a meat sauce. More tomato juice can be added for a larger quantity of sauce. Very good.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Combine soup, seasonings, lemon, pimento, mushrooms and 1/2 can onions.
Gently fold in seafood.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes. During last 5 minutes top with the other 1/2 can of onions.

title: blueberry boy bait cake
directions: Note:
Is using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Place 2 cups raw berries in crust.
In a saucepan, put 1/4 cup water, sugar, cornstarch, salt, butter, lemon juice and 2 cups raw berries.
Cook mixture until thick and pour over raw berries in crust.
Let cool and serve with Cool Whip.
Serves 6.

title: cornsticks
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and shortening.
Stir until blended.
Do not overmix.
Mix only enough to dampen dry ingredients.
Heat greased cornstick pans.
Pour in batter.
Bake in preheated very hot oven (450°) for about 20 minutes.
Yield:
8 large cornsticks.

title: tossed taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together right before serving.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Cut rhubarb into pieces being careful to retain the skin on each piece.
Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Put rhubarb into a 9-inch pastry lined pan and add the egg mixture.
Top with pastry, cut into fancy shapes. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking for 30 minutes until custard is set.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Chop, mix and drain first 3 ingredients.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Will keep 6 months in refrigerator.

title: cornmeal sour cream cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Cream butter and sugar. Add vanilla and pinch of salt.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, cornmeal and soda together 3 times.
Add sour cream.
Add salt to egg whites; beat until peaks.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: apple ringers
directions: Make syrup in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put syrup in pan and sit in oven while making rings.

title: mexican corn
directions: Drain corn combine in sauce pan with milk, butter, green chilies and cream cheese that has been cut into small pieces. Heat until cream cheese has melted.

title: barbecued pork roast
directions: Line baking dish with tinfoil.	Sprinkle dry onion soup on tinfoil and place roast
on top of soup mix.
Pour barbecue sauce over roast.
Cover	tightly.
Bake	at
300° for about 5 hours and separate with fork.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix well and shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Store in tightly covered container for three days prior to serving. Makes 50.

title: graham cracker candy
directions: Combine in a pan the butter, margarine and sugar; boil for 4 minutes.
Line cake pan (9 x 13-inch) with aluminum foil.
Spread whole graham crackers in bottom of cake pan.
Pour margarine mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts or pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool completely and then break into pieces.
Plain or cinnamon graham crackers can be used.

title: french bread
directions: In a large bowl mix 2 cups unbleached flour, 2 cups oat flour, salt and yeast.
Gradually add water and honey to dry ingredients. Mix well and let set 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup unbleached and 1/2 cup whole wheat flour, a little at a time.
Mix with electric mixer at medium speed as long as you can.
Stir in additional whole wheat flour, if needed, to make a stiff dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes. Let rise 20 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Form long thin loaves, taper ends and place on "Pammed" cookie sheet.
Take a serated knife and make slits 2 inches apart at an angle, cutting 1/2 inch into the dough.
Bake at 375° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: Combine dry mustard and cider vinegar and let stand overnight, beat eggs and add sugar; mix well.
Combine all ingredients and place in top of double boiler, bring water to boil and lower to medium.
Cook, stirring constantly for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Select melon with deep rind.
Remove all green rind and pink meat.
Cut remaining rind into 1-inch squares.
Soak this overnight or at least 8 hours in lime water.
Drain fruit and place in preserving kettle.
Cover with water and boil until easily pierced with a broom straw.
This usually takes 2 hours. Drain and cool fruit and stick each pieces with a clove.
Dissolve sugar and vinegar and add cinnamon.
Boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Add fruit.
Cook until rind is spotted, about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Line bottom of a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Whip powdered sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla for 15 minutes.
Line bottom of crust with 3 or 4 bananas, sliced.
Put whipped sugar mixture over bananas. Put drained pineapple over whipped mixture.
Whip 2 packages Dream Whip according to package directions. Put on top pineapple. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: mary beth's mother's pasta e fagioli
directions: Soak pea beans overnight.
Cook until tender, adding water as needed.
(If you cannot soak the beans overnight, add additional cooking time.)

title: country club squash
directions: Mix cooked squash and all other ingredients except bread crumbs.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish, greased.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and blend in vanilla.
Add flour and beat on medium high for 10 minutes.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake for 55 minutes to 1 hour.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients for 2 minutes (no longer). Remove from heat.
Melt in the peanut butter.
Add the vanilla, then add the oats.
Stir well.
Pour on waxed paper or drop by spoonfuls.
Yummy!

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil together all but marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and nuts until soft ball stage.
Then remove from heat and beat in chocolate chips and marshmallow cream; add nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish until cool.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Cap strawberries and chop up in mixing bowl.
Add strawberry glaze to strawberries and sugar and mix well.
Pull angel food cake in small pieces and put in dish; cover with strawberry mixture and spread Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon and add beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and place in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: quick bread and butter pickles
directions: In a large pan, place cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Cover with ice cubes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 3 hours or overnight.
Do not rinse!
Drain and add white vinegar, sugar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a rolling boil. Put in hot jars and seal.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti.
Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: essie's stuffing mix
directions: Partially cook celery and onions in water (just enough to cover).
Add margarine to melt. Transfer to large container and add all remaining ingredients. Mix and pour into a large buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large microwavable bowl on High 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in vanilla, marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Chill 1 hour.
Put 48 (1-inch) balls of dough into mini muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately place mini reese cup into each cookie.
Cool before removing from muffin tin.

title: barbecue sauce(for new england sauce)
directions: Melt margarine; add vinegar, then all other ingredients. Bring to a boil; let simmer over low heat for 5 minutes.

title: crispy roasted spuds
directions: Peel potatoes, slice lengthwise into eighths.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Roll potatoes in butter, arrange in pan and sprinkle with salt.
Combine flour and cheese; sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven, uncovered, for about an hour or until tender.
Turn potatoes in pan to coat.

title: cherry swirl
directions: Fold all ingredients together in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Other flavors of pie filling, such as strawberry, can be substituted.

title: oatmeal apple squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray Pam on 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan. Combine Butter Buds, brown sugar and granulated sugar in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Beat in Egg Beaters, apple juice and vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until blended.
Stir in oats, apples and raisins with a spoon.
Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown and toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Serve warm with cream topping (yields 4 dozen). Can be frozen.

title: grandma hebrlee's swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Use meat hammer and pound mixture into steak very good.
Cut steak in serving size pieces and brown in cast-iron skillet in hot grease.
Put into small oblong roaster pan.
Add 3 or 4 onions, sliced, tomatoes and peppers.
Put lid on.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: health soup
directions: Skim fat from top of soup first.
Put on to simmer.
Add any or all of the listed ingredients.
Add "No Salt".
Add seasonings to taste including sweet basil, tarragon leaves, lemon pepper and garlic powder.
Simmer about 2 hours.
May add bag of washed spinach the last hour.
It is low calorie, no cholesterol, high in nutrients and very satisfying.

title: heart healthy five-layered mexican dip
directions: Mix together sour cream and salsa.
In a shallow bowl, layer the ingredients, beginning with bean dip, then sour cream-salsa mixture.
Top with lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Garnish with chopped cilantro.
Serve with Guiltless Gourmet Baked Tortillas Chips.
One 2/3 c. serving contains only 3 gm. fat.

title: surprise biscuits
directions: Sift and measure flour. Cut butter into flour with pastry blender. Mix in sour cream. Mix well and drop into greased muffin pans. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 45 small biscuits.

title: ann's rigatoni ai 4 formaggi(rigatoni with 4 cheeses)
directions: Cook the pasta according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in a saucepan, melt the butter.
Add the Bel Taese, Fontina and Gorgonzola cheese, stirring until melted.
Blend in the cream.
Place the pasta on a large platter or bowl.
Add the sauce, tossing gently to coat the pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and ground pepper.
Serve at once.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: ten-in-one sandwich
directions: Slice French bread nearly through.
Mix together mayonnaise, mustard, onion, cheese spread and ripe olives.
Spread mixture between slices of the French bread so as to make 10 sandwiches. Insert salami between the spread.
Tie the loaf together with twine and bake uncovered for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 10.

title: museum chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill ingredients overnight and bake the next day. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.
Cover rim with aluminum foil to avoid pie crust browning too quickly.

title: dirty rice(good)
directions: Mix all together (raw) in pan.
Cover with foil.
Punch few holes in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake
as
directed
on
box, adding lemon jello to cake powder.
Slice bananas while cake is baking.
Drain juice off pineapple;	pour
over
sliced bananas.
Put pineapple in container until
ready
to	use.
While
cake
is cooling, mix vanilla pudding
as
directed on box.
If cake is baked in two layers, put
a layer in punch bowl by breaking cake in pieces. Add half
of pudding, half of pineapple, half of strawberries, half of bananas and
half of Cool Whip.
Repeat all the ingredients.
Put cake in refrigerator overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Here's the world's best potato casserole.
Mix hash brown potatoes, sour cream, grated Cheddar cheese, cream of mushroom soup and onion.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes, a little longer if you don't defrost the spuds first.

title: ham and onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Saute onions and ham 5 minutes.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine eggs, sour cream, mustard, celery seed, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add onion mixture.
Stir well. Pour in pie crust.
Top with other crust.
Crimp edges. Bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon garlic chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry. In a small bowl, mix together lemon juice, mayo, salt and pepper. Set aside. Slice garlic into slivers. Lift the top skin of chicken and tuck garlic slivers under skin. Fold skin back over and brush mayo mixture over skin. Place in a glass baking dish. Bake at 450 for 45 minutes. Chicken tops should look a little brown. Turn oven down to 375 and check for doneness after about 15 min.

title: butter bread sticks
directions: Melt in oven in pan 1/3 cup butter.
Remove as soon as butter is melted.
Sift ingredients together.
Mix together slightly and turn onto floured board.
Knead, roll out and cut into strips with floured knife.
Dip strips well in butter in pan and lay close together in pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 16 sticks.

title: santa's whiskies
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and make into two 2-inch rolls.
Roll the rolls in additional coconut.
Chill.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on cookie sheet at 370° about 12 minutes.
Do not brown.
Makes great Christmas cookies.

title: baked fish
directions: Roll fish in beaten egg and then in Ritz cracker crumbs. Place in shallow baking pan and bake at 350° to 400° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and brush with melted butter. Sprinkle almonds over fish. Bake 10 minutes more.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Pour into strainer and wash with hot water (this removes most of the fat).
Combine in a large saucepan or skillet the meat and the next 6 ingredients and 1 cup of water. Simmer.

title: light watercress soup(serves 4)
directions: Heat butter in saucepan.
When hot, add onion; cover and cook 2 minutes over medium heat.
Add potatoes and herbs; mix well. Continue cooking, covered, 3 minutes over low heat.
Pour in chicken stock, season and stir well.
Bring to boil and continue cooking, partly covered, 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add watercress to soup; cook 5 minutes.
Serve soup with sandwiches, if desired.

title: wine soup
directions: Bring the wine, water and spices to boil.
Strain.
Beat the egg yolks with sugar until lemon colored and slowly add the hot wine mixture, beating constantly until a thick foam forms at the top.
Be careful not to curdle the yolks.
Serve with wafers.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients. Shape into patties and fry as hamburgers.

title: creamy mexican party dip
directions: Chop tomatoes. Combine tomatoes, sour cream, green chilies and party dip mix.
Stir to blend. Chill for at least 1 hour.
Enjoy with chips and vegetables.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Salt chickens on both sides and place
on
large,
flat, ungreased pan, cut side up.
Combine
remaining
ingredients in saucepan.	Place on medium heat and blend	well.
Remove
from heat and brush chicken generously with
mixture,
using
pastry brush.
Place in 350° oven and bake 1 to 1	1/2
hours or until tender,
basting and turning chicken every 10
to
minutes. Oven may be turned up the last few minutes to brown if desired. Serve from pan or warm platter.
Serves 4 generously.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add corn, peas and carrots.
Put mashed potatoes on top.
Place in 350° oven to brown.

title: salmon spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve on low sodium crackers or bread that has been spread with low sodium margarine if desired.

title: mrs. perots' eagle brand milk
directions: Pour all ingredients in blender.
Whip until smooth. Ready to use in all recipes that call for Eagle Brand milk.
May be stored up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease and flour bottoms of 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and baking powder; set aside.
In large bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla, scraping bowl occasionally 3 minutes or until smooth and creamy.
Reduce speed to low.
Beat in mayonnaise until blended.
Add flour mixture in 4 additions alternately with water, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cornstarch.
Take small amount of mixture and make a thin paste with the cornstarch, then add cornstarch mixture to the remaining.
If you do this, it will not be lumpy.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Heat blueberries with 1/2 cup sugar in a saucepan until boiling.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk to make gravy consistency.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Pour blueberries in the middle of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done (brown) and knife comes out clean.

title: barbecue chicken arms
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: In a bowl, sift together dry ingredients. Squeeze orange juice into cup measure.
Add grated orange rind, butter and enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Combine orange juice mixture and egg.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients and stir only until dry mixture is dampened.
Add chopped nuts and cranberries.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Push batter up towards edges, leaving center slightly hollowed. Let batter stand for 20 minutes in pan before baking.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Cook in oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Mix crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and paprika.
Dip meat in egg and roll in crumb mixture.
Brown in hot oil.
Place spaghetti in a 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with meat and Mozzarella cheese.
Add tomato sauce combined with oregano and onion salt. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crab stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop up crabmeat.
Combine crabmeat, cream cheese and soup mix together with a hand mixer.
Set aside. Make a pocket in each chicken breast.
This is done by slicing horizontally, but do not cut all the way through.
Stuff each breast with the crabmeat mixture.
Coat each breast in flour, then eggs, and finally bread crumbs.
In a nonstick frying pan, heat up the olive oil and fry breast until golden brown.
Place breasts in an oven safe dish and bake for 30 minutes.
Allow to rest for 5 minutes and Dig In!

title: fresh or canned peach pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over peaches.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch inch pan at 375°, about 1 hour or until done.

title: great smoky mountain casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion in bacon fat.
Add tomatoes, sugar, ketchup and beans, without draining if canned.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spread your favorite cornbread recipe over.
Bake at 425° about 25 minutes. Bread on top will be like cooked cornbread.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Grease potatoes on outside before wrapping in foil and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
You will need 3 containers, one each for the crumbled bacon, the sour cream and the chopped onions.
Keep potatoes in foil and cut lengthwise inserting desired amount of butter, salt, pepper, onions, bacon and that heavenly sour cream.
This makes one wonder.
Do you eat to live or live to eat?
Anyway, it is a lot of fun to prepare this dish. Serves 6.

title: better-than-hostess cupcakes
directions: Mix cupcake batter as directed on box.
Put in paper liners in muffin tin.
Fill 1/2 full.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg and add chocolate chips.
Drop 1 teaspoon on each cupcake.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at temperature directed on cake mix.
No need to frost, filling will sink into cake.
Great for lunch boxes or picnics, no frosting to come off.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and make into 1-inch balls. Grease and flour cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
These can be frozen and reheated in a microwave for future use.

title: yogurt
directions: Heat milk to boiling point, at least 160°.
Add the condensed milk and cool the mixture to approximately 110°.
The secret is not more than 115°, or it will kill the culture.
You can test by putting your hand on bottom of pan.
If warm to touch, but not uncomfortable, it's okay.
Beat the yogurt; add a little milk and mix; then add it to the cooled milk.
Strain; pour into clean pint jars.
Immerse jars in pot of hot water (again, about 115°, no hotter).
Put lid on pot and stick it in oven for about 2 1/2 hours.
Do not have heat on in oven, although it could be slightly warmed while making the mixture, but be sure it is turned off. Refrigerate.
Beat with a fork slightly to make creamy before eating.

title: kraut chocolate cake
directions: Cream well butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Alternate water and egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir in kraut.
Turn into 2 greased 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Frost with mocha icing.

title: terry's burgundy beef stew
directions: Saute bacon.
Remove and save.
Season and flour beef cubes. Brown in bacon drippings.
Place in casserole with boiling beef stock, water and wine.
Put in oven.
Add spices including 1 onion impaled with garlic cloves.
Brown onions in drippings.
Continue to saute.
Add wine from time to time.
Reserve 1 cup wine.
Add onions last 1/2 hour.
Before serving, add mushrooms, last cup of wine and crumbled bacon.
Bake in 3-quart casserole at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: spicy chili con carne
directions: Brown hamburger, diced onion and diced green pepper in skillet.
Drain all grease.
In Dutch oven or large pot, combine hamburger (crumble into small pieces), onion, pepper and remaining ingredients.
Simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with cornbread or crackers.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add nuts, spices, soda and salt.
Add applesauce.
Add flour a cup at a time.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.
Batter will keep in covered container in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Raisins are good in these.

title: mama's green beans
directions: Fry bacon on in black iron pot.
Add green beans, water, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer one to two hours.
The secret of this recipe is cooking in the black iron pot.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard seed. While mixture is boiling, shred vegetables.
Pour over vegetables and mix well.
Let stand 3 hours and drain.
Put in jars and seal.

title: cherry salad
directions: Makes a large amount. RICH! You can also add chopped nuts, grapes, mandarin oranges.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Cut ham into bite size pieces.
Place in large saucepan.
Add jar of beans with juice, broth and water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with noodles.

title: spiced cranberry punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; let cool completely.
Strain, discarding cloves and cinnamon sticks.

title: crab newburg
directions: Melt butter in a 3 qt. saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour and spices; stir constantly and cook until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk and boil for 1 minute.
Stir in lobster and juice.
Serve hot inside split popovers.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook noodles in salted water and set aside.
Mix Ricotta cheese, 1/2 Mozzarella and cottage cheese and egg in bowl.
Stuff this mixture into tubes or shells.

title: slaw
directions: Chop the first 4 ingredients.
Add sugar (may use 1/4 cup sugar if desired), celery seed, salt and pepper.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift cinnamon and cloves with flour and sugar.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Mix together
ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured jelly pan at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Ice hot brownies.

title: lime jello congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, hot water, cold water and pear juice together. Mix cream cheese and pears to Jell-O mixture.
Add celery and pecans.
When congealed, cut in squares.

title: long pastrami sandwich
directions: Combine basil, oil and vinegar in a small bowl; set aside. Slice bread in half lengthwise.
With a spoon, hollow out bottom half, leaving a 1/2-inch thick shell.
In the shell layer 1/2 cheese, the pastrami and the tomatoes.
Top with the basil mixture and sprinkle with pepper.
Top with the remaining cheese and bread top.
Wrap in heavy foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or heat in covered grill for the same length of time or less.
To serve, cut crosswise into 4 to 6 slices.

title: broccoli topping
directions: Combine and let stand few hours. Pour over hot broccoli just as you serve it.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Combine mashed potatoes and sugar.
Add coconut, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Form into peaks on slightly greased surface. Allow to stand 20 minutes to dry.
Melt chocolate over hot water (not boiling) and dip base of each peak in it.
Allow to stand on wax paper until chocolate is firm.

title: aunt ginny's chicken dinner
directions: Fry chicken until brown; add all ingredients except mushrooms. Cook at least 1 hour or until tender.
Add mushrooms last 10 minutes.

title: jeanette lockman's cucumber relish
directions: Slice cukes and put in salt water for 6 hours, then drain and grind with red peppers and onions.
Put in kettle and squeeze out juice.
Then cover with vinegar (about 2 cups).
It doesn't need to cover as long as you can see the juice.
Then add sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric.
Boil 1 hour.
Seal while hot. This is very good!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie shells, together.
Pour into 2 chocolate pie shells.
Freeze.
Garnish with crushed salted peanuts, if desired.
Thaw slightly before serving.
Delicious!!! (Hershey's chocolate syrup may be added on top of each slice, if desired.)

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies (you may use an Osterizer or Ziploc bag with a rolling pin).
Set aside.
Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar in a medium bowl; set aside.
Mix milk and instant pudding per package directions or beat for 1 1/2 minutes. Add Cool Whip; mix until thick or for 1 minute.
Combine cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture.
Blend well.

title: peanutty snack mix
directions: Lightly butter jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Mix cereal, peanuts, raisins and banana chips in a large bowl.
Mix pudding and pie filling (dry) and honey in a small saucepan; heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Pour over cereal mixture; toss until evenly coated.
Spread in pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Break into bite size pieces.
Store snack in covered container at room temperature or in refrigerator. Makes about 10 cups of snack.

title: butterscotch bread
directions: Place frozen rolls in Bundt or tube pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar (and nuts, if desired).
Melt oleo in saucepan. Add brown sugar and pudding.
Stir until melted and hot.
Pour over rolls while hot.
Place pan in cold oven overnight.
Next morning, leave pan where it is.
Turn oven onto 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.
Invert on plate immediately.

title: homemade angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Into large bowl, sift together flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Sift again.
In clean, large bowl of standing electric mixer or in mixing bowl, place egg whites.
Using mixer on low speed, beat egg whites until foamy, about 1 minute.
Add cream of tartar and extracts.
Gradually increase mixer speed to high. While beating, sprinkle in remaining 1/2 cup sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
When all sugar has been added, use rubber spatula to scrape sides and bottom of bowl.
Resume beating at high speed until egg whites are stiff but moist.

title: never fail fudge
directions: In a large pan, stir together sugar, butter, milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Boil exactly 11 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off heat; add marshmallows, nuts and chips.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a large buttered pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients, except bacon, and form into two loaves.
This is fun!
(One can be frozen and served later.)
Place in tureens (if you have them, it makes a nice presentation) or 9-inch loaf pans.
Lay bacon strips on top to cover and bake for 1 1/4 hours.
Drain any accumulated fat. (There will be very little if you use the turkey variations.)
If serving cold, remove bacon and invert loaf; some jelly glaze will appear on the top.
Each loaf serves 8.

title: sweet potatoes and applesauce
directions: Layer potatoes and applesauce alternately in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with brown sugar and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until flavors are blended and top is brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese potato
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased casserole dish.
Add 1/4 cup milk before baking.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: grapefruit french dressing
directions: Cook sugar and water until syrupy.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until smooth.
Chill.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: *Put crackers into bread bag and roll to make crumbs.

title: dutch cabbage rolls
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper, rice and egg.
Mix well.

title: tea time tassies
directions: Blend together the cheese and butter, which have been softened to room temperature.
Stir in flour.
Refrigerate for one hour. Divide dough into 24 (1-inch) balls.
Shape each ball into a shell.
Place shells in mini-muffin cups or in small foil liners. Beat together the egg, melted butter, honey and vanilla.
Stir in half the ground pecans.
Sprinkle remaining ground pecans in the bottom of each shell.
Add a spoonful of the egg, butter, honey mix to each shell.
Top each with a pecan half.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes or until crust is golden.
You can use walnuts.

title: tuna pilaf
directions: Place tuna (drained) in saucepan.
Add onion, celery and mixed vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender, but not brown.
Add rice; mix.
Heat to serving temperature, stirring constantly. Makes 6 servings.

title: easy leftover fried rice
directions: Chop all ingredients in amounts comparable to leftover rice. Saute. Reheat rice in microwave and add to sauteed ingredients. Scramble 2 eggs in separate pan.
Add to rice. Add soy sauce to taste. Stir and serve immediately.

title: butter beans
directions: Add everything together and simmer (do not let come to a boil). Cook gently until beans are tender.
Add more warm water if needed to keep beans just covered.

title: brown derby cobb salad
directions: Place lettuce in bottom of a large shallow salad bowl. Arrange minced chicken in narrow strip down center of salad. Arrange strips of green onion, egg and tomato on one side; arrange bacon, Blue cheese and avocado (sprinkled with lemon juice) on the other.
Add salad dressing.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown beef on all sides.
Add water to mid-level of roast. Cook until tender, approximately 3 hours.
Add chopped, shredded cabbage, tomatoes with juice and sliced onion.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 1 hour. Good served with mashed potatoes.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Combine chicken, lemon juice, celery and grapes or pineapple. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Toss and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, or until well chilled.
Just before serving, fold cream into mayonnaise, then fold into chicken mixture.
Add almonds.
Serve chicken mixture on a bed of lettuce with garnish (grapes, grated orange rind, pineapple, etc.).

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add walnuts.
In mixing bowl, beat egg; add applesauce and melted shortening.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir just until blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan (about 8 x 4 x 4-inch).
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour. Cool on rack.

title: lentil soup
directions: Prepare lentils as directed on package.
In large pot put hocks and onion and fill with cold water.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add garlic and pepper to taste.
Add lentils.
Simmer until done.
After fully cooked, puree lentils to make a thick soup.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Combine ground beef, onion, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Shape in balls and place in greased casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Parboil 5 minutes; drain. Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in cooked rice, cheese spread and seasonings; fill peppers.
Place in baking dish; top with crumbs tossed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix together well the egg, sugar, shortening and milk.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 19 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool and frost.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients stirring well.
Store in a tight container.
Add 1/4 c. mix to every mug and finish filling with boiling water and marshmallows if desired.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain well.
Add tomato sauce, oregano and light seasoning to taste.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream and egg.
Blend well.
Grate Mozzarella cheese.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put tomato and hamburger mixture in layer first, then noodles, then tomato and hamburger, sour cream, cottage cheese and egg.
Continue layers.
Top with noodles and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut crunch bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter and cereal; pat into pan.
Let cool; top with 1/2 package of 6 ounce butterscotch chips and 1 (6 ounce) package chocolate chips.

title: chicken sesame
directions: Combine soup, milk and poultry seasoning. Blend well and set aside half of mixture. Mix cracker crumbs and sesame seed.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pa. dutch corn chowder
directions: Heat ingredients, but do not boil.
Serve with crackers. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cincinnati "three way" chili(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Pour water into large saucepan.
Crumble in beef (beef can be browned in saucepan first if you want to drain fat).
Add next 13 ingredients.
Simmer 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaves.
(Can be prepared up to 1 month ahead and frozen.)
Cook and place spaghetti on serving platter.
Pour chili over.
Top with cheese and serve immediately.

title: amaretto custard cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12 cup Bundt or tube cake pan.
Beat all ingredients in large bowl on low speed about 1 minute.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until done in middle, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pan and drizzle with glaze.

title: cornish hens stuffed with shrimp dressing
directions: Saute celery, onions and green pepper in butter.
Add mixture to wild rice; then add steamed shrimp and parsley flakes.
Mix well.
Stuff hens.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Boil together for 2 minutes the sugar, cocoa and milk.
Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour over vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together rice, milk and soups. Spread in bottom of large baking dish. Lay chicken on top. Bake at 350° for 2 hours, covered.

title: orange balls
directions: Let butter and juice soften at room temperature.
Add sugar and nuts to crushed wafers.
Add juice and butter.
Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls by pinching desired amount from mixture.
Roll in fine grated coconut.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix well and serve over ice.

title: nora june truitt's egg bread
directions: Mix together.
Beat well; pour in greased pan.
Bake in hot oven until brown.

title: brown betty
directions: Melt butter slowly, add bread crumbs.
Wash, core, pare and slice apples.
Place layer of bread crumbs in bottom of greased pan.
Cover with apples.
