Sprinkle with cinnamon, sugar and lemon extract.
Add layer of bread crumbs.
Cover remaining apples and rest of bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with water.
Bake in 400° oven 25 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with cream, ice cream or plain.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix chopped lettuce, drained oranges and almonds.
Toss with dressing.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to boil.
Add rice. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Boil sugar, peanut butter and syrup until melted together. Add Rice Krispies; stir together.
Add chips; stir until creamy.

title: frijoles refritos con queso
directions: Wash beans; simmer in 1 1/2 quarts of water 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add salt during last half hour of cooking. Drain beans, reserving liquid.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and paprika until smooth.
Add nuts.
Shape into roll and roll on waxed paper liberally sprinkled with paprika.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Slice and serve on crackers.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream the butter or margarine and sugar together.
Beat until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Add sifted dry ingredients and chocolate syrup alternately, blending well.
Blend in vanilla and chopped nuts. Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Spread with Lemon Glaze when almost cool.

title: icicle pickles
directions: You will need a stone jar.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Combine sugar, salt, shortening and scalded milk.
Let cool. Dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water and add to milk mixture.
Stir in the flour to make a dough just stiff enough to barely handle.
Let rise in a greased bowl covered with tea towel. Work down when doubled in size and let rise again.
Shape into rolls and put in greased pans.
When double in size, bake at 400° to 425° for 12 to 20 minutes, depending on size of the rolls.

title: "yankee" chili
directions: In large kettle, brown ground beef and onion in oil.
Drain well.
Add tomato sauce, ketchup, tomatoes and kidney beans.
Stir well over medium heat until blended.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Cover pan.
Turn heat to low and let simmer at least one hour, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sea foam frosting
directions: Mix egg whites, brown sugar, salt, and water together in top of double boiler.
Beat over boiling water for 7 minutes or until peaks form.
Remove from water; add vanilla and beat one more minute.
Frosts a 2-layer cake (very good on chocolate cake).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs; add milk, bread, salt and mustard.
Add sausage and then cheese.
Bake in greased 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes before serving. This may be made up ahead and kept in fridge overnight.
Leftovers reheat well.

title: baked cheese hominy grits
directions: Bring milk to boil; add butter.
Stir in grits.
Resume boiling; stir until mixture takes on look of cooked farina.
Stir in Gruyere cheese; season with salt and pepper.
Beat with mixer for 5 minutes.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until golden, about 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Melt butter and cheese.
Mix potatoes, butter, cheese, sour cream and onion together.
Place in casserole dish overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until warmed completely.
Really a favorite of our family picnic!

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and Eagle Brand milk in microwave on Medium power, stirring often, until well blended.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Add nuts and mix well.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: macaroni cheese dish
directions: Cook macaroni. Melt butter in pan. Blend in flour and gradually add milk. Cook until thick and starts to boil. Add cheese. Stir until melted. Remove from heat. Mix with macaroni. Bake in 3-quart casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in saucepan. Boil for 3 minutes. Then add the oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Drop by spoon onto a greased pan.

title: green beans, wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Combine rice with all ingredients but cheese.
Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan. Spread cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand before serving.
Freezes and keeps well.

title: p.d.q. supper
directions: In a 9 x 10-inch iron skillet, arrange Spam in center.
Place onion slices between Spam slices.
Pour beans over all and cover well.
Drizzle barbecue sauce on top.
Heat in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated throughout.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts. Shape into ball. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: sponge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes, until cake is browned and knife comes clean.
Great in Bundt pan.

title: golden cream potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine the ingredients, except milk, flour and cheese.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Fry pork until crisp; remove bits of pork and set aside.
Add 1/2 cup clam juice, 1 1/2 cups water, potatoes and onion to fat. Cook covered 15 to 20 minutes.
Add clams, 1 3/4 cups milk and cream.
Blend 1/4 cup of milk and flour; stir into chowder.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Add teaspoon of salt and dash of pepper.
Add some of the reserved pork to taste.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: "leah's" candy popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn.
Place in a large mixing bowl. Cook sugar, Karo and oleo to hard crack stage.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Pour over popcorn.
Mix well.
Spread out on buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool. Store in airtight container.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in a shallow casserole. Combine olive oil, soy sauce, honey, thyme, cayenne pepper, vinegar, allspice and pepper and pour over chicken.
Marinate in refrigerator for about an hour (overnight if you wish).
Bake chicken for 30 to 45 minutes or until cooked through.
Surround chicken with sliced mushrooms.
Spoon
the sauce over them and bake 5 minutes more.

title: quick oven meal in one
directions: On a large piece of foil, place hamburger patty.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and top with a slice of onion.
Slice a medium potato on top of the hamburger.
Add some salt, pepper and onion. Slice a large carrot on top and fold up foil tightly.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: creamy almond chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
In large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in all other ingredients (except rice).
Pour over chicken.
Cover and cook in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Prepare rice according to directions on box.
Serve each breast on mound of rice.
Serves 6.

title: lime salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise with cream cheese. Add jello and hot water. Stir until gelatin is dissolved. Add marshmallows and stir until they are dissolved.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Keep stirring as mixture is setting.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Mash softened cream cheese with a fork.
Add 1/2 c. mayonnaise and blend well.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Add chopped salad olives and olive juice.
Add dash of pepper.
Stir well. Refrigerate.
Spread on wheat or rye crackers.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil the chicken in 4 cups of water and seasoning.
Remove chicken and debone.
Boil spaghetti in same water as chicken. While spaghetti is boiling, saute onion, bell pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Mix sauteed vegetables with spaghetti still in the water, Ro-Tel tomatoes, chicken and Velveeta cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Pour mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: delicate lemon squares
directions: Combine and mix well the first 3 ingredients.
Pat into greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine Milky Way bars and butter and melt over low heat. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into greased 12-cup Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Cake tester should come out clean.
Remove from pan and cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and shortening until well blended.
Stir in milk,
flour and nutmeg one at a time until smooth.
Roll and cut. Fry in hot oil.

title: beef enchilada casserole
directions: Soften tortillas in beef broth, one at a time.
Grease an oblong pan (11 x 9-inch cake pan) with Pam.
Cut tortillas in small pieces and line the bottom of the pan.
Cook meat and onion until well done.
Add green pepper, chilies, can of tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Add both cans of soup and chili powder. Cook and mix well.
Make the layer of tortillas, layer of meat mixture, layer of cheese (grated) and so on until the next layer of cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan and unroll crescent dough.
Press seams.
Spread meat mixture over top.
Spread most of the cheese over meat. Crumble Doritos and sprinkle over cheese.
Remaining cheese goes on top of crumbled Doritos.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes, covered and 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and pepper in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and add all other ingredients, except 1/2 of cheese and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and crumbs on top. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple, then mix with jello and cottage cheese.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Do not need to use all 8 ounces of Cool Whip; adjust according to taste.

title: pumpkin nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually. Cream till light and fluffy. Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well. Sift flour, baking powder, salt, and spices together. Stir in dry ingredients and mix until blended. Add raisins and nuts. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes on greased cookie sheets.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix and let stand several hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook the noodles and drain.
Brown the ground beef and onion in frypan while noodles drain and cool.
In a large oblong pan put a little thinned sauce, a row of about 5 noodles, edges overlapped.
Dab on ricotta or cottage cheese, sprinkle with grated mozzarella.
Pour on some sauce and sprinkle with grated Parmesan.
Repeat these layers 4 or 5 times, ending with noodles on top, with some sauce over them.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup of mayonnaise with the milk and hot sauce.
Add seasonings; mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in mix. Roll in crumbs.
Place chicken pieces on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into shell.
Bake 45 minutes or until firm at 325°.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut flour, baking powder, salt and shortening with a fork, then add your buttermilk.
Mix together until it forms a dough. Roll out onto wax paper with rolling pin.
Place over pie pan and shape into pan, cutting off excess on outer edges.

title: allagash salad dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add oil.
Blend until smooth.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Hand stir in carrots and walnuts.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Place cottage cheese, lemon juice, mayonnaise and buttermilk in blender and blend thoroughly until creamy smooth.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: meat and cheese dip
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Brown ground meat; add onion, garlic salt, chili powder and pimento.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Combine both mixtures in chafing dish or fondue pot.

title: pecan snack
directions: Mix gently; spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.

title: sunrise squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble and cook sausage in medium skillet over medium heat until browned.
Drain off any drippings. Spread bread cubes in greased 11 x 7 baking dish; top with sausage, peppers and cheese.
Wash eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard until well blended.
Pour over cheese and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serve hot.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Melt shortening in large skillet.
Add meat, garlic, sugar and soy sauce.
Cover and cook over high heat for 5 minutes.
Add Chinese vegetables, peppers, tomatoes, salt and pepper; cook for 5 minutes more.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch in 1/4 cup cold water.
Garnish with cut up green onions.
Serve over fried rice.
May also sprinkle with Chinese noodles.

title: cranberry-apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry. Stir together the flour and sugar.
Layer apples, cranberries and flour mixture into pastry-lined pan.
Dot with 1 to 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Cover with crust; cut slits, seal, etc.
Dot top with 1 to 2 tablespoons of margarine. Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 425° until bubbly.
If desired, cover edges with foil until the last 15 minutes to prevent excessive browning.
Best served with vanilla ice cream.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter.
Beat eggs, sugar and flour.
Add chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Bake in a buttered pie pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until done; drain.
Cream with 1/2 stick margarine and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Pour in baking dish.

title: orange cream cookies(biscotta di arancia e crema)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
Cut in butter
with pastry cutter to resemble course breadcrumbs. Add sugar
and
mix
well.
Add
prebeaten eggs, milk, orange extract and orange peel to flour mixture.
Stir to form a soft dough. Knead
dough on floured surface until smooth.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Lightly grease one baking sheet.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Using biscuit
cutter dipped
in
flour,
cut
out
circles.
Place circles on
baking sheet.
Continue
until dough is finished, re-rolling as needed. Bake
at
350° for 15 to 20 minutes and lightly golden.
Cool completely on wire cooling rack.
Makes 20 to 25 cookies.

title: eagle brand milk substitute
directions: Warm blender jar with hot water first.
Put boiling water in warm blender and add butter first, then sugar and milk.
Blend briefly; scrape down sides of blender, then blend until completely smooth, about 30 seconds.
Pour out and let stand until cool and thickened.
Use immediately or refrigerate, covered, until needed.

title: honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in order given. Bon appetite!

title: marmalade cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put oil in mixing bowl.
Add brown sugar.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add egg and beat until thick and creamy.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Mix well with rubber spatula.
Place dough about 2 inches apart on buttered and floured cookie sheet.
Press in center with finger and place marmalade in each well.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: southern pralines
directions: Combine sugars, syrup and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Cool 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat by hand about 2 minutes.
Add pecans and beat until mixture is not glossy.
Drop by tablespoons on buttered aluminum foil.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Brown onion in butter; drain and save.
Saute mushrooms; set aside.
Brown meat in same pot.
Return onions to pot; add seasonings, bouillon and 1/2 cup sherry.
Cover and simmer gently for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
During the last half hour, add remaining sherry and mushrooms.
If desired, gravy may be thickened with a paste of flour and water.
When almost time to serve, add sour cream and reheat slowly.
Do not boil.
Serve with French bread, wild rice and salad.
Serves 6.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Combine drained corn, salt, sugar, pepper, flour and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until an inserted knife comes out clean.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Serve
with raw veggies or crackers.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Mix all together and dip cleaned shrimp into the batter.
Drop shrimp into hot oil and fry.
If batter is too stiff, add more milk.
If it is too dry, add more meal.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine first hash browns and onions; bring to boil about 30 minutes. Add celery soup and milk; salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and celery soup.
Mix in with chicken.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers.
Melt butter and pour over top.
If you want to pour a little bit of broth on top, you can.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil. Beat in eggs. Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together with milk and nuts. Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Note:
Broken California walnuts may be substituted for pecans.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Grate cheese and let soften. Cream together with 1 cup margarine. Add salt and cayenne pepper. Add flour, Rice Krispies and green chili. Form into balls (I drop by spoon). Press flat. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: sour cream rhubarb squares
directions: Cream together brown sugar, shortening, egg, sour cream and rhubarb.
Stir in flour and soda.
Turn in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with crumb topping.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and onion fine.
Bring sugar, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Let cool.
Combine oil and seeds.
Mix everything together and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Steam broccoli or cook in boiling water until tender.
Drain. Arrange on bottom of greased baking dish (large size oblong).
Cut chicken in pieces and spread on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, salad dressing and lemon juice.
Pour evenly over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and cover with buttered bread crumbs. (Crusts of bread, toasted and buttered, make a delightful topping.)

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and beat 2 minutes.
Grease and flour tubular, Bundt, 9 x 13-inch or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except beef, 1 cup tomato juice and onion slices.
Mix well.
Add beef; mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Pour 1/4 cup tomato juice over top, then lay slices of onion on top, then pour rest of tomato juice over all.
Bake 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Break lettuce up in a bowl.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add seasoning mix to it and cook according to the package.
Add other ingredients but the chips.
Add chips when ready to serve; mix all together.
Taco sauce can be added to give special flavor.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread and cube.
Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan and put cubes in bottom.
Cube ham and cheese.
Put on top of bread. Slightly beat eggs and add milk, mustard and pepper.
Pour over bread, cheese and ham.
Let soak 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
(Can also be made the night before and kept in refrigerator until morning.)

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix cream cheese and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and salt and blend.
Add vanilla and pecans.

title: spinich dip (light)
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger with onion. Drain mixture well and add pizza sauce and cheese. Put on bottom of bun and add a slice of Mozzarella cheese on top; heat in oven until cheese is melted. Makes 18 burgers.

title: baked beans
directions: Open beans and drain off juice.
Cook bacon and save fat. Pour drained beans in large baking pan.
Add ketchup, onion, salt, pepper, hot sauce, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and bacon fat.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Lay cooked bacon on top of beans.
Bake another 10 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloins side by side in large roasting pan. Wrap bacon across both, tucking the ends under the tenderloins. Combine rest of ingredients; pour over top. Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours. Baste often with juices during cooking. Can be marinated for several hours or baked immediately.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Grease dish; line dish with potatoes.
In separate pan, heat soup and water.
Add cheese and melt, then add sausage, pepper and pimento.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: Add nuts to melted butter.
Add flour.
Press into baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes (should be light brown); cool. Cream the cheese with sugar, vanilla and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding according to package directions. Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Garnish with nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: kheer raga(sweet rice pudding from india)
directions: In a saucepan, scald the milk.
Add rice and stir. Bring to a boil again.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 1 hour or until rice is soft and mixture is thick.
Add the sugar, saffron, cardamom powder and salt. Stir until the sugar is dissolved. Add dried fruit and cook until soft.
Add fresh fruit. Chill until ready to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Bring to boil; stir in water, stirring constantly.
Mix together cornstarch, flour, salt and milk.
Pour in butter and brown sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Remove and add 3 beaten egg yolks.
Boil for 2 minutes. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Cover with beaten egg whites.
Bake until top is brown.

title: banana bran bread
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
In separate bowl, combine bananas and cereal; let stand 2 minutes.
In large bowl, beat oleo and sugar together.
Add eggs and cereal to mixture.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture and nuts.
Put in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about one hour, until it tests done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from the pan.
Cool on a rack.

title: biscuits cake
directions: Mix together sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into 4ths, place in margarine then roll in sugar.
Place in a well greased tube pan and sprinkle pecans throughout cake as you build it.
Bake in 300° to 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sauteed zucchini with mushrooms
directions: Cook garlic clove in sesame oil in a large skillet, stirring constantly until tender.
Add zucchini.
Slice mushrooms, finely chopped basil, salt and seasoned pepper.
Cook 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chopped tomato and cook, stirring constantly until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with cheese and croutons.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: crackers burgers
directions: Crush crackers.
Then mix all ingredients together and let stand at least 30 minutes. Make into patties and brown in corn oil.
Makes a great burger.

title: rolled oats cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, then add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt, sifted together.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Don't overbake!

title: zucchini patties
directions: Let grated squash with salt set for 30 minutes, then drain well.
Mix in the eggs and flour.
Drop by spoonfuls to make little pancake type patties and fry until golden brown on each side.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Mix cranberry halves with powdered sugar and let stand while preparing muffin mixture.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and melted shortening all at once.
Mix until dry ingredients are dampened.
Do not beat.
Fold in sugared cranberries.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: orange date cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and rest of ingredients, beating slightly after each addition.
Add small amounts of flour at a time.
Beat well.
Blend in dates and nuts.
Bake 1 hour.
While cake is warm, pur over mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and juice of 1 orange.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand at least 4 hours before eating.

title: spaghetti squash with tomato sauce(low-fat)
directions: Place spaghetti squash halves, cut side down on waxed paper on bottom of microwave oven.
Cook on High 16 to 20 minutes, rearranging squash twice. Let cool 10 minutes.

title: lemon sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside. In a large bowl, beat sugar and shortening until fluffy. Beat in eggs. Stir in dry ingredients, then ReaLemon brand concentrate lemon juice.
Mix well. Chill 2 hours.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls. Roll in additional sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheets. Flatten. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 8 dozen.

title: coke cake
directions: Heat water, cocoa, coke and marshmallows to boiling.
Set aside.
Sift flour in lg. bowl.
Add sugar and salt.
Pour boiling mixture over flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and bake in oblong cake pan for 35-40 minutes in 325 degree oven.

title: better-than-sex chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Immediately after you take cake out of the oven, poke holes in top of cake with handle of wooden spoon and pour caramel over hot cake.
Chill cake until completely cool. Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle crushed candy over top.

title: corn cake
directions: Mix together, except cheese, and put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Last 15 minutes, top with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: brown rice with kale
directions: Cook rice following package directions; set aside, covered. Saute red pepper and garlic in oil in large skillet until tender, 5 minutes.
Stir in kale and broth; cook, covered, for 5 minutes. Stir in rice and lemon juice.
Heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican shrimp
directions: In large skillet cook together onion, celery and bacon until bacon is cooked.
Add flour and chili powder; mix well.
Slowly pour in water, cook about 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, peas and sugar, cook 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp is warmed through.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: four cheese pasta
directions: While pasta bows are cooking, combine the other ingredients in a saucepan and cook on low heat for 5 to 10 minutes.

In a 13 x 9-inch pan, pour a thin layer of sauce mixture, 1/3 pasta, 1 cup Ricotta cheese, 4 slices Mozzarella cheese, 1/3 pasta, 4 slices Swiss cheese, 1/3 pasta, remaining sauce and top with 4 slices Provolone cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes until casserole is hot and bubbly.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in punch bowl, except champagne. Stir until lemonade is dissolved.
Add champagne to mixture. Garnish with orange slices and cherries.
Serves 30 people.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out water.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: favorite green salad
directions: Toss gently in big salad bowl. Chill and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: instant pound cake
directions: Place ingredients in large bowl.
Beat 10 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Place in cold oven set at 350°.
Bake 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Pour
rest
of
corn
mixture on top to seal cheese in. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Boil linguini; rinse in cold water.
Mix all dressings together.
Put linguini and vegetables in bowl.
Pour dressing over all and mix.

title: company chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Spread rice and onion mix in bottom of Pyrex dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice and soup mix.
Pour water over this.
Pour melted margarine over all. Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Heat and pour over jello to dissolve. Add cream cheese and mix well; cool.
Add fruit, pecans and Cokes.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: cherry supreme cake
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with 2 cups of cold milk; beat until thick. Blend in the cream cheese, then add the sour cream.
Beat all ingredients together until smooth and free from lumps.

title: adult strawberry flips
directions: Blend the strawberries on high speed until pureed.
Put the eggs, lemon juice, sugar and vodka in blender to blend with berries, 15 to 20 seconds.
Pour into tall glasses over cracked ice.
Should serve 8.

title: louis' favorite chili
directions: Combine ingredients in large pot and cook for at least 1 hour to blend flavors.

title: almost chicken and dressing
directions: Make cornbread as usual.
Crumble baked cornbread.
Melt 1 stick butter and pour over breadcrumbs.
Layer in greased casserole dish, beginning with cornbread crumbs, then chicken mixture, then topped with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until browned.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover with aluminum foil the first 45 minutes.
Cook, uncovered, the last 45 minutes, basting with juices.

title: brie appetizer
directions: Prick top of cheese thoroughly.
Spread marmalade over top and sprinkle with almonds.
Place on baking sheet and bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese oozes out.
Serve with any bland crackers.

title: texas cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses; beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Cover with finely chopped pecans. Makes approximately 12 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Beat together shortening and 1 1/4 cups sugar in a large bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour mixture.
Combine remaining sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Roll dough into balls.
Roll each ball into cinnamon mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Bake pie shells.
Cook other ingredients on stove top until thick.
Pour into cooked shells.

title: swedish creamed potatoes
directions: Heat margarine in 12-inch skillet until melted.
Cook potatoes and onion, uncovered, in margarine over medium heat, turning frequently, until potatoes are light brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add 1 cup half and half.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.
(Add 1 to 4 tablespoons half and half if necessary.)
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Blend in cocoa and vanilla.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, onion, celery, hard-boiled eggs and bacon.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Coarsely shred cabbage in 5-quart Dutch oven over medium heat in hot oil.
Add salt and cook until tender.
Brown meat and onion, add spaghetti sauce, water and rice.
Heat to boil, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Top with half cabbage, 1/2 remaining meat and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat, layer with cabbage, meat sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can be made ahead, just increase baking time to heat through.

title: smoked beef spread
directions: Mix and heat 20 minutes at 300° to 325°.
Very good on snack rye cocktail bread.

title: pecan chews
directions: Add sugar and eggs to melted butter.
Mix well.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Fold in chopped pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with PAM.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in boiling water until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and place
in
casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet, cook margarine with onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Add potatoes and cook about 10 more minutes.
Cover.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; stir to crumble.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: scalloped squash
directions: Drain and mash squash.
Brown onions in butter and add eggs, milk and crackers.
Mix and season with salt and pepper.
Bake 30 minutes in covered dish.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients as for cookies.
Cook and let cool. Mix the next 3 ingredients; cook until thick.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick; spread with date mixture.
Roll like a jelly roll. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk; stir.
Knead on board for 30 seconds. Roll.
Cut in squares.
Peel and core apples.
Place part of apples in each square.
Put 1 tablespoon sugar, dash of nutmeg and cinnamon in each crust.
Bring dough around apples.
Press edges together.
Place in baking dish.

title: shrimp and rice pie
directions: Mix cooked rice and shrimp with fork and place in baking dish. Mix salt and pepper with milk and pour over shrimp and rice; sprinkle vinegar over surface.
Divide butter in small pieces and dot over top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: delicate pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 13-inch pans. Prepare cake as directed on package.
Divide batter evenly in pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Follow package directions for doneness test and cooling.

title: special k bars
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt together the chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Spread over top of other ingredients.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into bowl.
Add orange juice, grated rind (and water) and shortening.
Stir.
Add the beaten egg, cranberries and nuts.
Put in greased 9 x 5 x 3 -inch loaf pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix well all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not open the stove door!

title: cheesy chicken crescents
directions: Combine chopped deboned chicken and grated cheese.
Open crescent rolls into triangles.
Place approximately 2 tablespoons of chicken/cheese mixture on "fat" side of crescent triangle. Fold over the
2 short "legs" and then roll down the long leg of crescent triangle to form a pouch.
Combine soup and milk to make sauce.
Pour 1/2 of sauce into Pyrex baking dish.
Place pouches in dish and pour the rest of the sauce over them.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes (until tops of rolls are toasted).
Top with cheese!

title: teriyaki potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; scrub thoroughly with a vegetable brush.
Cut tiny new potatoes into quarters or the medium potatoes into 1-inch pieces.
Place potatoes in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole. Add margarine or butter, teriyaki sauce, garlic salt, Italian seasoning, black pepper and red pepper.
Toss to combine.
Cover; micro-cook on 100% power (High) for 12 to 15 minutes (14 to 16 minutes for low-wattage ovens) or until potatoes are tender, stirring twice during cooking.
Stir before serving.
Garnish with snipped rosemary and serve with sour cream if desired.
Makes 5 side dish servings.

title: diabetic smothered onions
directions: Slowly heat margarine in large skillet.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes or until onions are nicely browned.
Makes 10 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the oil and sugar together.
Add eggs, then pumpkin. Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture; beat well.
Add nuts.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans about 15 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Yields 3 cups.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thick on a floured cloth covered board. Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until light brown. Makes 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: hummus
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Then put in a bowl and drizzle with olive oil.
Add parsley, if desired.
Dip Syrian bread into this.
It's great!

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Beat evaporated milk, lemon juice and pinch of salt.
Mix Jell-O and sugar so it will cool while you beat milk, lemon juice and pinch of salt.
Whip milk, lemon juice and pinch of salt until stiff and then add the Jell-O and milk.
Use wafers for the crust.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Butter a 9-inch tube pan and dust the bottom and sides with the cocoa.
Heat the coffee and bourbon in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add the chocolate and butter; cook.
Stir in the sugar; let stand 5 minutes and transfer to the bowl of an electric mixer.
Sift the flour with baking soda and salt.
Beat into the chocolate mixture on low speed in 4 parts. Add the eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth and pour into the tube pan.
Bake the cake about 1 1/2 hours, until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let cool on a wire rack before unmolding.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with whipped cream.

title: fruit cocktail pudding dessert
directions: Mix together flour, salt, soda and white sugar. Drain juice from fruit cocktail, reserving 1/3 cup. Mix egg, brown sugar and reserved juice together; add to flour mixture. Fold in fruit and nuts. Spread in a greased 9 x 13 inch baking pan and sprinkle 1/4 cup brown sugar over all. Bake 40 minutes at 325°. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler being careful not to let steam in.
Make peanut butter crackers as usual and dip in chocolate to coat.
Cool on wax paper.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Fill with whole milk to freeze line.

title: submarine sandwiches
directions: Brown onions, celery, and meat.
Add seasonings, mustard and ketchup.
Cook about
10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add egg. Mix well.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Heat milk,
soup
and
Velveeta cheese in top of double boiler until
cheese
melts.
Add	chilies and pimento.
Brown meat and onion; add grated Longhorn cheese.	Fill each tortilla with
meat mixture.
Roll tightly and place in long baking dish.
Pour cheese
sauce
over
the top of filled tortillas. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a full boil over medium heat.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Pour into long greased cake pan.
Cut.
Cool.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Mix flour and cream in saucepan.
Add margarine and cheese. Melt on lowest heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until thick, stirring occasionally.
Keeps several weeks in refrigerator.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs together.
Add flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Roll into balls and then roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons white sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: wiener casserole
directions: Mix all together and let set an hour or more.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini and pasta
directions: Bring a pot full of water to a boil.
Break up the vermicelli and cook until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Spray pan with olive oil Pam and saute onions, peppers, zucchini and garlic until fork-tender.
Toss with pasta and add butter, then coat with Parmesan.

title: rice pie
directions: Cook rice until almost done.
Drain, but don't rinse.
Add hot milk and let stand until milk soaks in.
Add salt and butter. Set aside.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients
to boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and soda.
Stir and pour over corn and bake at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour out on counter top and let cool, approximately 1 hour.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Make dough of all ingredients except nuts and raisins. Divide dough into 2/3 and 1/3 parts. Put nuts in 1/3 part and raisins into 2/3 part. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: rice and lentils(rich in vitamins)
directions: Heat oil.
Saute onions.
Add water and vegies; salt and pepper.
Simmer over low fire until soft (30 to 50 minutes). Preparing in advance enhances flavor.
Serves 4.

title: tallfrina
directions: Brown ground beef, then add bell pepper and corn.
Let this mixture cook a while.
Saute onion, all tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Let cook about 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook noodles, drain.
Then combine all ingredients, except cheese and olives; salt and pepper to taste.
Add cheese, saving enough for top of casserole.
Add stuffed olives.
Mix cheese and olives to the mixture. Cover top of casserole with cheese and olives.
Bake in slow oven (350°) until brown and cheese is bubbly.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate syrup.
Beat 5 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Pour two-thirds of batter into a greased and floured
10-inch
tube
pan or Bundt pan.
Add chocolate syrup
to
remaining
batter.
Mix
well. Pour
over
batter
in
pan.
Zigzag spatula through batter to marbleize.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Process or grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and put in cookie press or roll thin and cut into strips about 4 inches long.
Bake in oven at 350° until light brown.
Makes about 100.

title: beef and vegetables
directions: Cook meat in pan with olive oil.
Add salt, pepper, broccoli, mushrooms, onion and beef broth.
Heat through, then add sour cream and serve over cooked noodles.

title: cranberry christmas salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3/4 cup water.
Mix in cranberries and pineapple.
When Jell-O is set, top with mixture of cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Serve.

title: honey lime fruit salad
directions: Mix honey, limeade concentrate and poppy seed in medium bowl. Carefully toss fruit and honey mixture.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together and put in a covered container.
Use a heaping teaspoonful in a cup of hot water.
Red hots may be added for more flavor.
This mix will keep a long time in the refrigerator.

title: spaghetti soup to can
directions: Make tomatoes to juice.
Cook the spaghetti.
Melt butter and fry onion in it, then add hamburger.
Chop celery fine and cook; also cook the carrots.
Soak beans overnight and cook until almost soft.
Mix this all together.
Put into jars and cold pack for 2 hours.
Makes approximately 35 quarts.

title: sauce for green beans
directions: Mix all together and serve on green beans.
Also good as a dip.
Best when made a day before for flavoring to go through.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice raw, peeled potatoes into casseroles.
Put in dish. Cook butter, flour, salt and milk until thick.
Add cheese, cut into small pieces.
Pour mixture over potatoes and cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Stir occasionally.

title: low-fat lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add vegetable oil and next 4 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer for 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.

title: wine
directions: Put all ingredients (except balloon) in jug.
Fill with lukewarm water.
Anchor balloon on top of jug; it will expand. When balloon starts going down, wine is ready.

title: vegetable bars(low-fat)
directions: Roll out flat on a cookie sheet the pizza crust.
Bake 8 minutes at 425°.
Mix the following ingredients: cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Chop up fine 3/4 cup of each of the following: green onion, tomato and carrots.
Spread the cream cheese mixture over the baked dough.
Shake all vegetables together and spread over the cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle 1 cup grated no-fat Cheddar cheese on top.
Put wax paper over top and press firmly.
Refrigerate 2 hours and cut into bars. Makes 18 bars.
Seventy-three calories and 1 gram fat per bar.

title: chinese tuna
directions: Mix well and place in baking dish.
Cover with potato chips or cracker crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and salt.
Beat until stiff.
Add M&M's or nuts or chocolate chips.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
(Do not grease.)
Drop cookies on sheet.
Turn off oven!!! Leave overnight.

title: brown sugar coffee bars
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, eggs, soda and salt; mix well, then add flour and cup of coffee and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Sprinkle crushed walnuts and package of chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple nightmare cake
directions: Mix eggs with oil or butter.
Add to dry ingredients. Gradually blend in 1 cup water.
Pour into ungreased angel food pan.
(Dotty uses large rectangular pan and greases it and adds 2 layers of waxed paper on bottom to remove cake easily from pan.) Bake at 350° for 1 hour (35 minutes for rectangular pan).

title: london broil
directions: Mix all ingredients except steak.
Brush top of steak with half of mixture.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn, brush other side and broil 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Slice thinly on diagonal and serve with Mushroom Sauce.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and mushroom soup in baking dish. Put onions or bacon pieces on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: summer crab mold
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; whisk in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Gradually whisk in milk to make white sauce.
When thickened, stir in cream cheese.
Soften gelatin in water and add to hot mixture; stir to dissolve gelatin.
Remove mixture from heat.
Stir in mayonnaise, celery, crab and onion. Add salt and hot pepper sauce to taste.
Rinse 4 to 5-cup mold with cold water.
Fill mold with crab mixture.
Chill until firm. Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Heat oven to 300°. Beat egg white until soft and foamy. Combine all remaining ingredients, except nuts; whisk into egg white. Stir in nuts until well coated. Spread mixture in single layer onto an ungreased baking pan. Bake nuts for 15 minutes, then remove from oven. Using a metal spatula, toss, stir and separate nuts. Reduce oven temperature to 250° and return nuts to bake until medium brown, about 10 minutes. Remove from oven; toss and stir again. Place baking pan on wire rack to cool. Break up any nuts that stick together. Store in an airtight container up to 2 weeks.

title: shrimp goulash
directions: Put oil, garlic, sausage or Spam in skillet and stir-fry 1 minute.
Add peppers and stir-fry 1 or 2 minutes.
Add raw peeled shrimp and stir-fry until shrimp are done.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken in water.
Salt and pepper until done.
Remove chicken from broth and debone and place back in broth.
Add margarine and soup.
Cook until well blended, then simmer while making dumplings.

title: orange thyme chicken(makes eight 3-ounce servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken pieces in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place thyme over chicken.
Combine chicken broth and juice.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Cover chicken with foil.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until tender and juices run clear.
Discard thyme.

title: easy salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape into 6 patties.
Brown patties in skillet; spoon off fat.
Stir in remaining soup and mushrooms.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Heat oil in a Fry Daddy or large pot.
Flatten biscuits and put a hole in center with your finger.
Ask an adult to gently lower dough in oil; it may splatter.
Turn over when it begins to brown. Cook until second side is brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serves 20 hungry first graders, but it's best to have extras on hand!

title: snowball cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour; then add flour with nuts, stirring with a spoon.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar and store in an airtight container.
Make ahead for holiday treats.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 large loaves or 3 small ones.
Cool in pans for 20 minutes before taking out of pans.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Bring soups and V-8 juice to a boil.
Add vegetables and beef; simmer at least 1 hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in a large dish as listed.
Refrigerate.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and crumbs.
Stir.
Add corn, onion, seasoning and butter; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel and slab potatoes into thick slices, uniform in size. Cook in salted water with onion that has been sliced.
Cook until tender but firm.
Drain well.
In casserole dish or pan, add half the cheese and butter.
Add potatoes, then rest of cheese and butter.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until melted.
Stir.
Is easy to double and can add more or less of anything to suit taste.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Combine eggs,
raisins	and vanilla.
Let stand 1 hour. Cream sugars
and oleo.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in eggs, raisins,
nuts
and
oatmeal.
Dough
will be stiff. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: "frozen" coconut cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix according to directions on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
While cake is baking, boil together the sugar, water and 1/4 cup coconut.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add the coconut flavoring.
Punch holes in hot cake; pour syrup over cake while it is still hot.
Cool thoroughly.
Frost with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut.
(Cool Whip and coconut can be mixed together before frosting, if desired.)
Refrigerate frosted cake overnight.
It's moist and g-o-o-d.

title: macaroni salmon loaf
directions: Heat milk and bread crumbs.
Stir in egg yolks (beaten).
Add macaroni and salmon, cream, butter and salt.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Fill buttered tin (loaf pan size) and sprinkle with paprika.
Set in hot water and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole and add 2 cups corn.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in pan of hot water.

title: light dessert
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces and layer in the bottom of a large bowl.
Cover cake with yogurt.
Layer with sliced berries and top with Cool Whip.
Repeat layers until bowl is full.
Let set 2 hours before serving.
You can use different flavor yogurt and berries to personal preference.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix in order in blender until well blended.

title: fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar, cocoa, butter, vanilla and salt.
Bring to a boil at medium-high temperature for approximately 25 minutes, testing by drops of this mixture into a cold cup of water.
When it forms a soft ball stage, remove from heat.
Pour mixture into 2 (9 x 9 x 2-inch) buttered glass pans, stirring into each pan 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Chill.
Cut in squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs until well blended. Add bananas and beat. Add sugar, oil and nuts. Beat until well mixed. Add dry ingredients and mix. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven 55 to 60 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove from pan and let cool on wire rack.

title: bride's punch bowl
directions: Fill Tupperware jello ring with ginger ale and strawberries. Freeze until ready to serve.
Mix Hawaiian Punch, remaining ginger ale and strawberries in punch bowl.
Add ice ring at serving.

title: basic bundt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; beat 15 minutes. Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°F.

title: mexican salad
directions: Chop lettuce and tomato in deep bowl.
Mix in beans that have been drained and grated cheese.
For salad to be crisp, wait until ready to eat to add Fritos.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles, then drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Top with 4 slices cubed bread. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: apple betty
directions: Mound apples in a baking dish and sprinkle with orange juice. In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Mash margarine in with the dry ingredients.
Sprinkle dry ingredients over apples. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple whip salad
directions: Blend cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Stir in dry jello.
Fold in orange sections and pineapple tidbits.
Chill overnight.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in cold Coke.
Add pecans and cheese.
Refrigerate until set.

title: glazed popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a large bowl.
Heat butter and syrup in a saucepan over low heat.
Stir in granulated sugar and gelatin; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer gently for 5 minutes. Immediately pour this mixture over popcorn, tossing it to coat well.
Spread popcorn on aluminum foil lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Spread evenly.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan and break into small pieces.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: lasagna(no meat)
directions: Cook lasagna.
Place layer of lasagna in cooking dish.
Add sauce.
Add a layer of mushrooms, sprinkled with Parmesan cheese. Layer with shredded Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, beginning with lasagna.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: oven seafood spread
directions: In medium bowl, blend cream cheese, green onion, pepper, lemon juice, salt, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in crab, shrimp and clams.
Turn mixture into a 1-quart ungreased casserole ovenproof serving dish.

Sprinkle almonds over top. Bake in a 350° convection oven on rack 3 for about 30 minutes (or bake in preheated 350° radiant bake oven about 30 minutes) or until bubbly around edges and center reaches 130° to 140°.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: If desired, according to taste, add 1 small onion and 1/2 green pepper, chopped.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: praline bars
directions: Break the graham crackers apart and line bottom of 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan with them.
Bring butter and sugar to a boil and boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour evenly over crackers.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Let cool a few minutes and lift out with spatula onto waxed paper or foil to completely cool.
Yields 40 bars.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix with pastry blender.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: poppy seed pound cake(fat free)
directions: Blend cake mix and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and blend for 6 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crush Oreos, mix with melted butter.
Put layer in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix instant pudding with 3 cups cold milk; set aside. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add Cool Whip and pudding. Layer Oreos, then pudding mix in pan.

title: good hot rolls
directions: Put milk, Crisco and sugar in pan; warm it up enough to melt Crisco; set aside to cool.
Dissolve yeast in the 1/2 cup warm water.
Sift flour.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and cover with a wet cloth.
Let rise and then put in the refrigerator.
When ready to use, roll out, cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted butter, fold over in half.
Press edges in place in order to hold together.
Let rise again before baking at least 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: apple and butterscotch chip cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and salt together. Combine sugar and oil in large mixer bowl; mix well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour mixture, beating until smooth.
Fold in apples and walnuts.
Pour into oiled 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with butterscotch chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: lasagna spinach roll-ups
directions: Puree tomatoes in blender until smooth; set aside.

Cook sausage, onion and garlic in Dutch oven until meat is browned. Stir in pureed tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce, mushrooms, 2 tablespoons of parsley, oregano, basil, pepper, Tabasco and bay leaf.
Simmer, partially covered, 45 minutes.
Remove bay leaf. Drain and squeeze water from thawed spinach in sieve.
Combine spinach, 2 tablespoons parsley, Ricotta, Mozzarella, eggs, 4 tablespoons Romano, salt, pepper and nutmeg in a bowl; mix well. Spread 1/3 cup filling on each noodle; roll up.

title: super quick brownies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together in microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in sugar, then all the other ingredients. Microwave in an 8-inch glass pan on High for 5 1/2 to 6 minutes. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mints
directions: Mash cheese.
Add flavoring and coloring.
Mix in sugar. Knead with hands until it is like pie dough.
Make into balls (marble size) and dip in granulated sugar; press in mold.
Unmold at once.
These are so nice for holidays!

title: skinny french fries
directions: Wash and prepare the potatoes.
Dry the surface of the potato strips by placing them on paper towels.
Spray a nonstick cookie sheet with Pam butter flavored cooking spray.
Spray the potatoes with Pam and then sprinkle them with seasoning of choice.
You might try shaking them in a clear, plastic bag.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until tender and golden brown.
Turn occasionally with a spatula.
Serves 4.

title: five star hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook and reduce cream over moderate high heat for 15 minutes. Whisk in dark sugar; whisk until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolates and stir until melted.
Whisk in butter and whisk until smooth.
Add flavoring if desired.
Store in fridge.
Warm before serving.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cajun fried turkey
directions: Remove the giblets, neck and wing tips from the turkey for making the stock.
It is best to plan on frying the turkey outside on a butane cooker with a 12 to 15 gallon pot.

title: barbecue hash
directions: Mix everything together in frying pan on the stove, except the beef.
Cook for 20 minutes on low to medium heat.
Add beef and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in oven and drain.
Add this to all other ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: polka dot meat cups
directions: There's no need to grease the muffin cups for these individual meat loaves.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup until mixture spins a thread.
Add 2 cups raw Spanish peanuts.
Cook until mixture turns a light golden brown.
Add margarine, vanilla and baking soda.
Mixture will fluff up when you add the baking soda and mix.
Pour quickly onto Teflon or buttered cookie sheet.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Bake at 325° in a 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan for 30 minutes.
Check to see if done, if not bake 5 minutes more.
Don't bake too long or it will be dry.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine cereal, milk and 1 cup of the tomato sauce.
Add ground beef, eggs, oregano and salt.
Mix well.
Spoon meat mixture into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Invert meat loaf onto warm serving platter.
Heat remaining 3/4 cup tomato sauce and spoon over meat loaf.
Serves 8.

title: microwave chili con queso
directions: Using a microwave-safe container, combine Ro-Tel tomatoes and one pound Velveeta cheese, cut into 1-inch squares.
Melt on High for 2 minutes.
Extra time may be necessary on some microwaves. Stir at the end of 2 minutes and remember that the food still cooks after the microwave stops.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
You may substitute different pie fillings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given and top with additional cracker crumbs mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 400° until bubbly and brown.

title: ham steak with pineapple
directions: In a small bowl, mix pineapple juice with mustard and honey. Place ham steak on rack in broiling pan and spread with 1/2 of mustard mixture.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn steak, top with pineapple slices.
Spoon remaining mixture over pineapple.
Broil 4 minutes longer or until pineapple is lightly browned.

title: post thanksgiving turkey casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine turkey, celery, mayonnaise, onion and lemon juice.
Top with almonds, cheese and noodles.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: chinese chicken and snow peas
directions: In a mixing bowl, toss the chicken strips with the cornstarch. Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a wok or frying pan until hot. Stir-fry the chicken pieces in the wok until golden, about 5 minutes.
Remove the chicken to a warm plate.
Heat the remaining oil in the wok and add the celery, onion, garlic and ginger; stir-fry until fragrant, about 4 minutes.
Add the chicken broth and simmer 4 minutes.
Add the snow peas, soy sauce, water chestnuts and chicken strips.
Cover and cook about 2 more minutes, or until the chicken is reheated and the snow peas are crisp-tender.
Serve immediately over hot rice.
Yields 4 servings.
Serving size:
2 cups over 1/2 cup rice.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Roll crackers to a fine meal.
Add all fruit and nuts.
Heat milk until you can dissolve the marshmallows in it, stirring constantly.
Pour over mixed ingredients.
Mix real well using hands if needed.
Pack back in cracker box, lined with wax paper. Wrap in foil to store in icebox.
I make mine 2 to 3 weeks before Christmas.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and water.
Blend dry ingredients, except nuts and raisins.
Add pumpkin and blend.
Add nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.

title: dip for fresh veggies
directions: Combine and refrigerate overnight.

title: peppery beef and vegetables
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain well.
Keep warm for sauce.
In small bowl, stir together water, soy sauce, cornstarch, pepper and red pepper.
Set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add pumpkin and dry ingredients together with water.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: whipped horseradish sauce
directions: Mix the cream cheese, horseradish, sugar and salt together. Whip the cream and fold gently into the cheese mixture. Refrigerate.

title: apple cinnamon pancakes
directions: Mix together flours, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon. Combine the beaten egg whites, milk, margarine and applesauce. Stir into the flour mixture just until moistened.
Pour batter from pitcher or large spoon onto hot griddle.
When pancakes are puffed and full of bubbles, turn and brown the other side. (Griddle 350°.)

title: cajun-style orange roughy
directions: Sprinkle fish fillets with cajun spices.
Coat more heavily for a stronger flavor, if desired.

title: savory pecan roast
directions: Combine.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Turn onto platter.
Serve with a mushroom sauce or other favorite gravy.
Serves 8.

title: banana-strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the sour cream.
Chill till slightly thickened.
Add 1/2 of mixture to bottom of 9 x 13 glass pan.
Then put a layer of sour cream, 1 pint.
Put the remaining jello mixture on top.
Chill.

title: texas cheese casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Pour 1/2 of the meat mixture into a 2-quart casserole. Top with 1 cup coarsely crushed corn chips and 1/2 cup cheese. Pour rest of meat on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: angel biscuits(or piazza base)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast into warm water.
Combine yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Combine this with dry ingredients.
Roll out, cut, fold and dip into melted butter.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: sour cream cheesecake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into spring-form.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.*

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, 1/4 pound cheese,
egg,
onion,
cilantro
and pepper.
Mix well. Shape into loaf
in
1 1/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or to desired doneness.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine remaining
cheese,
cilantro
and
milk
in saucepan;
stir
over low
heat until smooth.
Pour over meat loaf.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cherry coconut cake
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over mixture.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut over this; top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey barbecue
directions: Cut up turkey.
Mix ingredients together in large size pan. Allow to simmer for a couple of hours (the longer the better).

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. Add milk.
Stir in beaten egg and oil.
Toss in blueberries and 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: easy beef and pea pods
directions: Spray saute pan with Pam.
Brown steak in pan on medium heat. Combine gravy mix with water and add to browned steak.
After gravy thickens, add water chestnuts and place frozen pea pods over top of steak.
Do not mix.
Pea pods will steam cook in about 3 to 4 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks; stir and serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 5.

title: pierogi
directions: Mix together.
Cover.
Let rest for 15 minutes before shaping. Cut round circles out with a large glass.
Fill with desired filling. Pinch closed.
Cover and let rest.
Pinch side again before boiling.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Mix margarine, milk, brown sugar and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla. Blend in enough confectioners sugar for good spreading consistency.
Makes enough for a 2 layer cake.

title: easy vegetable squares
directions: Crust:
Unroll crescent rolls and pat into 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix ground peppers, onions and pepper and drain.
Add to vinegar mixture and boil for 30 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar with mixer (not blender). Add oil slowly, beating constantly and continue to beat until thick.
Add poppy seed and paprika and beat for a few minutes. Keep in refrigerator.
Yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: steven's holiday pumpkin cookies
directions: Option:
Can replace chocolate chips with chopped walnuts.

title: cranberry pork roast
directions: Place roast in slow cooker. In a medium bowl, mash cranberry sauce. Stir in sugar, mustard and cloves. Pour over roast. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until tender. Remove roast and keep warm. Skim fat. Measure 2 cups of the liquid (add water if needed) and pour into saucepan. Bring to boil over medium heat. Combine cornstarch and cold water to make a paste. Stir into a gravy. Cook and stir until thickened. Season with salt.

title: honey-lime butter
directions: Beat all ingredients in a small bowl until well blended. Makes about 3/4 cups.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Whip the egg with the powdered sugar.
Add melted butter, melted chocolate, milk and a little vanilla.
Whip with electric mixer until creamy and thick for spreading.
Have your mixing bowl in pan of ice and water while you beat icing.
Keeps perfectly for days.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Beat butter, confectioners sugar and eggs with mixer until it forms a custard.
Roll wafers moderately fine and fill 13 x 9-inch pan with layer of wafers, then custard, berries and whipped topping.
Place layer of wafers on top.
Cool in refrigerator 8 hours.

title: play dough
directions: Mix well. If sticky, add more flour. Add food coloring for different colors.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
(I use egg substitute Egg Beaters.)
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.

title: jalapeno-mesquite burgers(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix A.1. bold steak sauce with ground round (or extra lean hamburger).
Deseed and dice jalapenos (discard seeds).
Cut shoots from green onions and dice into fine chives.
Add Mexican seasoning, diced jalapenos and chives to meat/A.1.
Mix thoroughly, kneading until greens are evenly distributed.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Stir in onion and beef.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons skim milk if needed to thin dip.
Chill 1 hour.
Serve with veggies.

title: tunisian zucchini
directions: Steam or microwave zucchini.
Combine olive oil and lemon juice, then garlic and caraway seed; salt and pepper.
Drain zucchini and place into server.
Pour dressing over zucchini and mix.
Top with paprika.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all together; add 4 eggs and beat 1 minute. Then add milk, melted margarine, vanilla, salt, baking soda and cinnamon. Cook at 350° until done.

title: salmon tacos
directions: Preheat oven to 180°C.
Place taco shells on tray and crisp in oven for 6 to 7 minutes.
Peel, stone and slice the avocado.
Brush sides with cold water to prevent discoloration.
Fill taco shells with layers of avocado, lettuce, salmon, tomato and cheese.
Top with hot sauce before serving.
Makes 12 tacos.

title: cocktail crab dip
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spread almonds in a flat pan and bake for 10 minutes.
Remove when browned.
Combine all other ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Place almonds on top.
Bake for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: penny's cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients for cake.
Mix next 2 ingredients and swirl into cake mixture.
Bake at 325° to 350° approximately 20 to 25 minutes (according to cake instructions).

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Boil carrots in boiling water (salted) until tender.
Drain well.
Layer carrots and pepper in a bowl.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over all.
Let marinate in refrigerator 24 hours or more.

title: ham bake
directions: Add macaroni and 1 teaspoon salt to 6 cups boiling water; stir.
Boil rapidly for 7 to 10 minutes; drain.
Add 1/4 cup margarine or butter, 1/4 cup milk and the Kraft grated cheese; mix well.
Add the ham cubes, green pepper, 1 cup milk and beaten eggs.
Prepare dinner as directed.
Add ham and green pepper; season to taste.
Place in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Combine milk and eggs; pour over dinner mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Stir into creamed mixture.
Form into balls about the size of walnuts. Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place about 2-inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Dissolve sugar in syrup.
Add peanut butter.
Pour over Special K cereal.
Mix.
Press into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips over hot water or in microwave.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Cut into bars when set.

title: granny cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Beat eggs well and add pineapple.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients and beat well. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with mixer.
Fold in pineapple.
Put in refrigerator. Serve with butter crisp or Town cracker.

title: bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine cereal and buttermilk.
Let stand 5 minutes until cereal is softened.
Add oil and eggs.
Blend well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Stir in flour and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Batter can be baked immediately or stored in tightly covered container in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Pour on top of melted oleo (do not stir). Pour fruit on top of flour mixture; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour in casserole dish. Top with sour cream, then Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Butter 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Place cooked broccoli in casserole and top with chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry, then pour over chicken.
Cover with cheese.
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs; pour on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes (usually 45 minutes), uncovered.

title: party squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender.
Mash fine.
Butter a casserole.
Layer dressing, then other ingredients.
Put dressing on top.
Dot with butter and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine; add sour cream, then sugar, a half cup at a time.
Alternate eggs and addition of 1/2 cup flour, finishing with eggs, beating well after each.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
(Two loaf pans can be used for baking also.)

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in heavy skillet or saucepan. Cook over high heat until sugar dissolves, then add peanuts.
Turn heat to medium and cook for about 10 minutes or until syrup darkens. Add soda and stir. Work quickly and spread thinly on greased cookie sheet. When cold, break into pieces.

title: mocha icing
directions: Cream butter until light and smooth.
Gradually cream in cocoa; add vanilla and then coffee alternately with confectioners sugar to make icing stiff enough to spread.
Spread on cake.
This may be made ahead of time and kept in a covered bowl.

title: pork chop dinner(crock-pot)
directions: Add all ingredients to large crock-pot.
Add tomatoes last. Cook for 6 hours on medium temperature.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage and onion; drain.
Spread refried beans in a deep dish or flat glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread meat mixture over beans.
Scatter jalapeno peppers on top, then shredded cheese.
Top with hot sauce and bake for 20 minutes at 400° or until bubbly.
When done, quickly top with any or all of the following:
sour cream, chopped avocado, sliced olives, chopped tomatoes, Chinese parsley, green onions and guacamole. Serve with tortilla chips as a dip.

title: crab cakes
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together egg, mayonnaise, mustard, pimento, parsley, Old Bay Seasoning, worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, pepper and salt. Add crab meat and 1/4 c. saltines. Toss the mixture gently. Spread remaining 1/2 c. saltines on a plate. Form crab mixture with a 1/3 c. measuring cup, gently into eight 3/4 inch thick patties. Coat the top & bottom of each patty carefully with the saltines, transferring the crab cakes to a sheet of waxed paper. In a large skillet, heat oil and butter over moderately high heat until the foam subsides. Saute crab cakes, in batches if necessary, 1-2 minutes on each side, or until they are golden. Transfer them as they are cooked to a heated platter. Serve crab cakes with lemon wedges.

title: gran's artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Decrease time if baking in more than one small casserole dish.
An onion soup bowl works well.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: mystery cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Bring the remaining ingredients to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Combine both mixtures and quickly drop on waxed paper.

title: broken window glass salad
directions: Prepare orange, strawberry and lime Jell-O separately, using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water per package.
Pour each flavor into an 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm or overnight.

title: glazed fresh apple cookies
directions: Heat oven to
Sift
flour with baking soda.
Mix shortening,
brown	sugar,	salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and egg until
well
blended.
Stir in half of flour mixture, then nuts, apples
and
raisins.
Blend
in
apple
juice, milk or cider, then remaining flour mixture.
Grease cookie sheet and drop rounded
tablespoons of dough 2 inches apart.
Bake 11 to 14 minutes or until done.

title: texas straw hats
directions: Fry onion and celery in oil until tender. Add hamburger, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, tomato paste and water. Simmer 1 hour, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Serve over corn chips and top with grated, shredded cheese.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients into bowl or container.

title: confetti coleslaw
directions: In a salad
