bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, apples and onions. (At this point, you may cover and refrigerate for up to 2 hours.) In a medium-size bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and tarragon; mix until well blended.

title: crispy chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: In shallow dish, beat egg.
Dip chicken into egg.
On waxed paper, coat chicken with bread crumbs.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-low heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 15 minutes or until browned on both sides and no longer pink.
Remove; keep warm. Pour off fat.
In the same skillet, combine soup, milk and water. Heat through, stirring occasionally. Spoon soup mixture over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with rice.

title: party mix
directions: Mix vegetable oil and ranch dressing.
Shake all ingredients in paper sack.
Store in air tight container.

title: eggnog parfait pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Cut ice cream into chunks and add to hot Jell-O. Stir until melted. Chill until partially set. Add nutmeg and flavoring. Stir in egg yolks. Then fold in egg whites. Pour into shell. Chill until set. Top with whipped cream and maraschino cherries.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice.

title: custard pie(this is a tasty custard pie.)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl, except for nutmeg.
Place in an uncooked pie shell, sprinkle nutmeg on top, and bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake for an additional 45 minutes.

title: zucchini hot cakes
directions: Mix altogether and drop from tablespoon in frying pan with small amount of hot oil.
Fry until golden brown on both sides. Powdered sugar may be sprinkled on top.

title: grape-nuts ice cream(easy)
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Very good.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients after you have drained and boned salmon. Put in refrigerator to chill.
Roll in 1/4 cup chopped pecans and enough parsley to roll in.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweeney salsa
directions: Gently combine ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken chipotte
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
In a blender, puree garlic, peppercorns, cloves, cumin and 1/4 cup onion with 1/4 cup of water.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add sliced onions.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add puree.
Cook over medium heat.
Heat 10 minutes. Add tomatoes; bring to a boil, then simmer 5 more minutes, covered. Puree chiles with remaining water; add to skillet.
Boil 2 minutes. Collect seasonings.
Add to chicken, cover and cook over low heat for 25 to 30 minutes until chicken is tender.

title: just like pasta house salad
directions: Tear lettuce into large mixing bowl.
Drain artichoke hearts. DO NOT USE MARINATED HEARTS.
Add sliced red onion and drained pimentos.
Add olive oil, vinegar, salt and pepper; toss.
Add cheese; toss again.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix and boil 2 or 3 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add all ingredients to slow cooker except macaroni and parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Turn control to high.
Add cooked macaroni cover and cook additional 10-15 minutes.
Sprinkle parmesan cheese on individual servings.

title: texas crab grass
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion, cheese and cooked and drained spinach and crab.
Serve warm with Triscuits.

title: alta's chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.
Place in casserole; top with cheese.
Cover.
Bake
at 300° for 2 hours.
This can be mixed up the day ahead and refrigerated overnight.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Fry, drain and crumble sausage.
Mix with cheese and sprinkle in unbaked pie shell.
Lightly beat eggs.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Double ingredients for 2 pies.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in pot of water.
Let sit while preparing the rest.
Beat eggs well in a large bowl.
Mix together sugar, salt, lukewarm water and melted shortening.
Add yeast and eggs.
Mix until dissolved.
Stir in plain flour.
Cover and keep in refrigerator at least 12 hours.

title: beef short ribs(prep time:  10 minutes.  cook time:  2 hours and 10 minutes.)
directions: In a large Dutch oven, heat the oil and brown the ribs on all sides.
Add the carrots, celery, onion and garlic.
Continue to cook for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the tomato paste and cook, stirring slowly, for 3 more minutes.
(Optional:
You can dust the short ribs at this time with flour to help thicken the sauce.)
Add the rest of the ingredients and cover.
Cook for about 2 hours on low heat (simmer) or until the meat begins to pull from the bone. When done, remove form the pan and strain the liquid.
You can now thicken the sauce or leave as is and season with salt and pepper. Serve with truffle mashed potatoes and haricots verts.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, vanilla, shortening and about half of the cake mix (dry) until light and fluffy.
Stir in remaining cake mix, the chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
(Cookies will be soft in centers when done.)
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: grandview fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Beat well.
Add cinnamon and the fruit cocktail (mixed together).
Mix in the nuts.
Add flour and other dry ingredients.
Put dough in the refrigerator and let set for 1 hour.
Grease a cookie sheet lightly and drop cookie dough by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° about 12 minutes (or less) until lightly browned on bottom.

title: dumplings with sauerkraut
directions: Cook the sauerkraut, adding just enough water to barely cover, for 20 minutes.
Mix the remaining ingredients; cook for 5 minutes with cover off and 7 minutes with cover on.

title: hot chinese mustard
directions: In a small saucepan, bring water to boiling.
Combine mustard, cooking oil and salt.
Stir boiling water into mustard mixture. Serve with fried wontons, egg rolls or burgers.
Makes 1/3 cup sauce.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix
sugar, cinnamon, allspice, mace and salt.	Stir in sweet potatoes.
Combine eggs, milk and butter to sweet potato mixture. Pour
into	shell.	Bake in a hot oven at 400° until filling is set.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: In measuring cup, mix the soy sauce and Italian dressing. Pour over chops and let stand for 2 hours.
Grill on inside or outside grill until done.
May substitute boneless chicken breast.

title: melt away cookies
directions: Sift together soda, cream of tartar and flour.
Soften margarine.
Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add vanilla and then eggs.
Blend together.
Add sifted ingredients and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 375° oven.
Do not overcook.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Layer onions and cabbage in pan.
Slice carrots on top of cabbage.
Sprinkle minced garlic on top and pour tomatoes over garlic.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Brown sausage and add to mixture.
Stir well and cook
2 more minutes.

title: chicken lasagne bake
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Drain, rinse, with cold water; drain again and set aside.
Combine soup, broth and salt stirring until smooth; set soup mixture aside.
Combine cream cheese and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in onion and next 3 ingredients.
Set cream cheese mixture aside.
Layer half each of lasagna noodles, cream cheese mixture, chicken and soup mixture in a lightly greased 8 inch baking dish.
Repeat layers. Combine bread crumbs and butter, sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 25-30 minutes. 12 servings.

title: cherry cake
directions: Spread cherries in
bottom
of	pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over cherries. Cut thin	slices	of
butter
and lay on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mustard-topped fish
directions: Sprinkle fish steaks with pepper.
Place fish on rack in broiler pan; brush with 1 tablespoon of the margarine.
Set oven control to broil.
Broil fish with tops 2 to 3 inches from heat until light brown, about 5 minutes.
Turn; brush with remaining margarine.
Broil until fish flakes easily with fork, 5 to 8 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in cheese, mustard and onions.
Spread mixture over fish.
Broil until tops are golden
brown, about 1 1/2 minutes.

title: baked beans(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Cook, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: mexican stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash, top and clean out peppers; set aside.
Dice onion and potatoes.
In a mixing bowl, combine meat, potatoes, corn, onion, salt and pepper.
Add 3/4 jar of salsa and mix.
Fill peppers.
Place in baking dish and pour remaining salsa on top.
Bake until peppers are soft (approximately 45 minutes).

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix altogether and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan kisses
directions: With electric mixer on high, beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat in sugar, vinegar and vanilla.
Fold in nuts.
Drop teaspoon of dough 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet while hot.
Sprinkle lightly with colored sugar.

title: no-sugar barbecue sauce
directions: Add all ingredients except butter and lemon to a small pot. Boil, then simmer until mixture quits boiling, add the butter and lemon juice.
Keep the sauce warm, and soak the meat in the sauce for a while before cooking.
Continue to keep warm and baste the meat as it cooks.
Cook chicken on charcoal for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, pork ribs the same.
Cook pork loin 4 to 6 hours, pork shoulder 24 hours.

title: sand cups
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add instant pudding mix.
Beat with whisk until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and half of crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into 8 to 10 (7-ounce) plastic cups.
Fill cups 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
You can decorate with miniature umbrellas, gummy seashells, worms, sharks, candy stars or chopped peanuts.

title: mushroom delight appetizer
directions: Blend all ingredients. Spread on English muffins. Cut muffins in quarters. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together the sugar, cornstarch and pineapple in casserole dish.
Mix oleo, cheese and crackers.
Spread over first mixture as a topping.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a tube pan or two 9-inch layer cake pans.
Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in nuts, carrots, coconut and pineapple.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour or in layer cake pans 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar coffee cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add and cut in shortening; set aside 3/4 cup to use as topping.
To remaining crumbs, add egg, sour milk, soda and cinnamon.
Mix to blend.
Spread in greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking pan and sprinkle with reserved crumbs and nuts. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: orange dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Line muffin tins (18).
Stir together flour, brown sugar, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, stir together milk, eggs, margarine and vanilla.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients; add milk mixture and stir just to combine.
Stir in chips.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from tins.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Combine nuts, sugar, salt and syrup in a 1-1/2 qt. ovenproof bowl.
Mix well and cook on High for 7-9 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Add butter and cook 2-3 minutes more until nuts are golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Add
soda and vanilla.
Stir; candy will become light and foamy.
Pour immediately onto a greased
cookie sheet. Spread as thin as possible.
Allow to cool and break into pieces.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook the spinach with butter for about 5 minutes.
Blend eggs and flour with mixer; add cheeses.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach 'n cheese grits
directions: Cook spinach with onions.
Drain.
Prepare grits according to directions.
Stir in spinach and remaining ingredients.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.

title: country potato soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in 3 tablespoons butter until golden brown.
Add milk and cook over boiling water for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook potatoes in boiling salt water for 10 minutes; drain.
Heat remaining 2 tablespoons butter and blend in flour.
Gradually stir in first mixture and potatoes.
Cook until thickened.
Season to taste.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: dump cake(easy and so good!)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Excellent as dessert!
Eat it, just plain or use whipped cream on top.

title: peach punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add remaining ingredients except Sprite.
Mix well. Freeze.
Add Sprite at serving time.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix together in a 5 x 7-inch cake pan (greased) all except cake mix and margarine.
Spread dry cake mix on top.
Chop margarine into small pieces and drop on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mound candy
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl well and shape into small balls. Then melt in top of double boiler 12 ounces chocolate chips and 2/3 block of wax.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and let cool.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Add cream cheese, eggs, sugar, evaporated milk and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour into all-ready made pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Take out and cool.
Add topping of your choice.

title: cinnamon fluff
directions: Mix together with enough milk to be like biscuit dough.
Put into an angel food or Bundt cake pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, cinnamon and dabs of butter either before or after baking.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in Cool Whip. Put in graham cracker crust.
Spoon 1 can cherry pie filling around the edge or put all over the top.

title: two-handed oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream eggs, brown sugar, peanut butter, baking soda, white sugar, vanilla and soft oleo with mixer.
Stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips and M&M's.
Drop on cookie sheet; flatten with glass, dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheap punch
directions: Mix punch and lemon-lime.
Put in sherbet.
Pour ginger ale over it.
Cake use 2 bottles of punch to make more.
The color will be between pink and red.

title: gingerbread men
directions: In
a
saucepan,
cream
margarine, sugar, molasses and spices;
mix
well.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium
heat.
Remove from heat and cool.
When lukewarm, stir in the eggs and vinegar.
Add the baking soda and flour.
Stir to form a smooth dough.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon meringue pie *
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; add boiling water.
Cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Add slowly a small part of hot mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Pour all together and cook about 5 minutes, stirring, or in double boiler.
Remove from heat and stir in butter, lemon juice and now, grated rind.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake in a moderate oven at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until as brown as you like.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Stir together sugar, oil, egg and vanilla.
Add milk and mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients, sifted together.
Fold in rhubarb and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until easy to mix. Add fruit and the powdered sugar (sweeten as desired by using more or less sugar).
Roll into a ball.
Roll in poppy seeds or nuts, or can be left plain.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill.
Will keep for several days, if refrigerated.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in a greased casserole dish 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: pittsburgh potatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Grate potatoes and add crumbled cheese and sour cream.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: stove top pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter
and
mix
in
sugar
in a 10-inch skillet. Arrange 4
drained
pineapple slices on this mixture and place cherries
in
centers.
Pour
cake
mix over pineapple slices. Cover skillet
and
place
on
electric burner at 250° (or for gas, over low heat) for 25 minutes.
Uncover.
Allow to cook 5 minutes
longer.
Invert
onto platter, allowing pan to remain in position for 1 minute.
Remove pan and serve.

title: "bird's nest"
directions: Place creamed potatoes on plate.
Take a spoon and make a hole in the middle of potatoes.
Fill hole with English peas.

title: mama's curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit and arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Serve with Fritos Scoops or your favorite chips.

title: coconut cream fudge
directions: Combine the butter, cream of coconut, milk, coconut flavoring, vanilla, confectioners' sugar and cocoa in large saucepan. Stir to mix.
Cook over low heat until butter has melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Pour into a buttered 8 inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm enough to cut into squares.
This fudge softens a little at room temperature so it is best to keep it refrigerated until you plan to serve it.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Bake desired amount of sweet potatoes until done.
Peel and whip with mixer until smooth.
Add the other ingredients to your taste.

title: parsnips
directions: Boil parsnips with sugar until tender.
Drain.
Put into baking dish.
Cover with bacon and drizzle bacon grease over top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into oblong greased casserole dish. Bake at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard and salt.
Blend in 2 tablespoons of the cider vinegar and grated onion.
Gradually beat in oil.
Beat until thick and light.
Slowly beat in the remaining cider vinegar.
Stir in celery seed.
Pour into a screw-top jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously to blend well.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Shake before using.

title: taco cornsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll pan, melt margarine in oven.
In mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Turn on a floured surface and knead 10 to 12 minutes.
Pat or roll into a strip, 3 x 24-inches.
Cut into 1-inch sections.
Roll each 1 x 3-inch strip in margarine. Arrange in pan. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until browned.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Add tomato sauce, sour cream and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Place in buttered casserole; cover with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cauliflower mountain(microwave)
directions: Place whole head of cauliflower, stem end down, in an 8-inch glass pie plate.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, or until tender.

title: layer cake
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Then add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 4 well-greased cake pans that have been dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: snowy mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
Mash with electric mixer.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic.
Beat on high speed until smooth and light.
Stir in chopped chives.
Spoon into lightly greased 8 to 10-cup casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until light brown and heated through.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli into bite-sized
pieces.	Cook
in salted water until barely tender.
Drain
and
cool.
Chop tomato and onion; drain tomato.
Toss onion,	tomato	and
broccoli
with enough mayonnaise to coat (about 1
cup).	Salt
and pepper to taste. Cover tightly and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: rocky road cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan (Baker's Joy is a joy!).
Mix the first 4 ingredients.
In another bowl, beat together the cake mix, eggs, mayonnaise and water until blended.
Stir in first mixture; pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until cake is done.
Dust with confectioners sugar after removing from pan.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Combine oil, sugar and melted chocolate and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place a thumbprint in cookie. Bake at 375° for 4 to 8 minutes on greased baking sheet.

title: texas taters
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and top with cornflakes mixed with oleo. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jay's parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese and salt in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time in a bag, coating potatoes well.
Melt margarine in a shallow baking dish.
Add potatoes and bake at 375° about 1 hour, or microwave by cooking on High for 11 minutes covered with wax paper.
Slip in regular oven to brown, about 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Take and grind up cranberries in grinder or Salad Shooter. Drain pineapple.
Combine cranberries, pineapple, 1 cup sugar, marshmallows and Cool Whip together in bowl and freeze for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, then serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a separate bowl and mix.
Add
dry ingredients to wet ingredients.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes. Pour
mixture 2/3 full into
ungreased
loaf
pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 loaves.

title: chocolate pecans
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler over low heat. Add pecans. Remove pecans, one by one, with a pair of tongs and place on foil until chocolate is cool.

title: black walnut and rum buttercream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour 3 cake pans (9-inch size).
Empty one box of cake mix into a large mixing bowl.
Add 4 eggs, 1/3 cup vegetable oil and half of the milk and water mixture.
Beat until the batter thickens for about 5 minutes.
Pour into a large bowl; set aside.

title: walnut cake
directions: Beat corn oil for 10 minutes.
Sift flour with baking powder. Add eggs; beat for 10 minutes.
Add walnuts, vanilla and flour. Blend.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased Bundt pan.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Dice carrots.
Cook in salted water until fork-tender; drain. Add chopped onion to melted margarine and saute for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients to diced carrots, reserving 1 cup of crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with 1 cup crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbling, about 20 minutes.

title: mashed potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk and add shortening, sugar, potatoes, eggs and salt.
When mixture has cooled to lukewarm, add dissolved yeast and mix well.
Add flour to make dough stiff.
Knead thoroughly until smooth.
Put in a large greased bowl.
Refrigerate until wanted.
Pinch off shape and let rise until double in size, 1 or 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fresh cranberry orange relish
directions: Slice unpeeled orange in 8 sections.
Remove seeds.
Place half the berries and half the orange slices in a food processor. Process until mixture is evenly chopped.
Transfer to bowl. Repeat with remaining orange and berries.
Stir in sugar.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: josh potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Slice potatoes in half and place in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan with skin side down.
Break up top of potatoes with a fork.
Top potatoes with butter or margarine, sour cream, ham, bacon and chicken.
Other ingredients can be substituted or deleted as desired.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 425° until all ingredients are hot.

title: sweet and sour pork or chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except meat, peppers and onion.
Mix until thick.
Pour over meat, then place onion and peppers on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: corn light bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat fat or oil in 8 x 8-inch cake pan in oven.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk.
Stir to mix.
Add heated oil.
Pour immediately into heated pan.
Bake about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: southern corn pudding(recipe originated with my grandmother)
directions: Use fresh or canned whole corn.
Combine all of the dry ingredients and add the milk.
Add this to the lightly beaten eggs.
Add melted butter and the corn.
Turn into a buttered casserole and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6.

title: mix-n-match squash casserole
directions: Place squash and a small amount of water in a large saucepan; cover and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Transfer to a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add soups, Ro-Tel, garlic and chili powder.
Place tortillas in chicken broth for 10 minutes.
Line long glass baking dish with tortillas, then layer of chicken, the soup mixture and cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix Wesson
oil and sugar.
Sift together cake flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry mixture to sugar and Wesson oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add shredded carrots.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions together.
Add rest of ingredients and cook down until thick on low heat.

title: zucchini soup
directions: In a 4-quart pan, saute the onions and zucchini in oil 10 minutes or until browned.
Add chicken stock; bring to boil.
Add lima beans and peas.
When mixture comes to boil again, reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are soft. Season with salt, pepper and cumin.
Puree in batches.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt choc. Chips, margarine and peanut butter together in microwave or over double boiler.
Stir together. Pour over the top of cereal in a large bowl.
Stir to coat. Put powdered sugar in and stir a little bit.
Transfer all ingredients to a large paper bag, fold down top and shake vigorously to coat.
Put back in bowl and freeze to enhance flavor.

title: coconut milk bread
directions: In one-half cup warm water, mix 1 teaspoon sugar with yeast. Let sit until yeast rises.
Remove coconut meat from shell; rinse and grate.
Add 2 cups warm water to pulp; mix and squeeze out milk.
Repeat with 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Discard pulp.

title: little braccioli
directions: Note:
If braccioli is unavailable, use sandwich steaks!

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together in a casserole dish.
Take 1 stack Ritz crackers and crush.
Melt 3/4 stick margarine.
Place Ritz crackers over mixture.
Pour margarine over crackers.
Heat oven to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple inside-out cake
directions: Combine sugar and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour, soda and beat well.
Stir in pineapple and vanilla. Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and top with frosting.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the butter and add gradually the sifted sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Sift together the dry ingredients.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw and drain vegetables.
Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: cinnamon cookie balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in flour.
Add pecans.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Dip into the cinnamon sugar mixture.
Cool on rack.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Boil the peppers 5 minutes. Brown the ground beef and onions. Drain.
Mix tomato sauce with water. Add onion and beef mixture with rice and half the tomato sauce, egg, salt and pepper. Stuff peppers.
Pour remaining sauce over top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: savory mushroom saute
directions: In 10-inch skillet melt butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients except parsley.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are tender (3 to 4 minutes).
Stir in parsley.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish; mix sugar, flour and juice of pineapple.
Add 1/2 cup of the cheese to mixture and the crushed pineapple.
Pour into casserole dish; add remaining cheese and cracker crumbs on top.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix everything together; put in casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple, add water to juice to total 3 cups.
Put juice in 3 qt. sauce pan, add sugar, Jello, and marshmallows. Bring to boil, and stir continuously until marshmallows melt.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and debone chicken; set aside.
Fry chopped onion in oleo until clear.
Add garlic powder and tomato sauce.
Simmer 12 to 15 minutes.
Add mushroom soup.
Add spaghetti which has been cooked in chicken broth.
Then add drained peas and chopped up chicken. Let simmer only enough to heat thoroughly, with as little stirring as possible.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape into one ball or two logs.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill.

title: vegetable pancake
directions: Mash vegetables together.
Beat in remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Remove when golden and place on paper towels to drain.
Serve with sour cream and sprinkle of paprika.

title: tangy slaw
directions: Heat mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, celery seed and sugar.
When sugar dissolves, pour over cabbage and toss.
Let set couple of hours.

title: tallerene
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add meat.
Stir and cook until brown. Add tomato sauce and 1 cup of water.
Add noodles and cook until tender.
More water may be added to keep moist.
Salt to taste. Add corn and olives.
You can add a little cinnamon for taste.

title: blueberry-bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and 1 cup milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs, butter and 1/2 cup milk; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Gently stir in cereal mixture and blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 2 dozen.

title: hot crab bake
directions: In a skillet, melt 4 tablespoons of butter; blend in flour. Add milk all at once.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in crab meat, eggs, pimiento, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Spoon mixture into 6 individual casseroles or baking shells.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 3 teaspoons sugar. Press into bottom of 13 x 9 pan. Cream together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread into pan. Combine jello, boiling water and frozen strawberries. Let set for 10 minutes, then pour over other layers and refrigerate.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Put this mixture into a pie pan and bake at 275° for 25 minutes, then 300° for 25 minutes more.

title: zucchini squares(appetizer)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes and cut into squares.
Yields 40 squares.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cut up broccoli and boil until tender.
Then in a different pan cook the onion in margarine until tender.
Gradually add flour.
Then gradually add milk, broccoli, cheese, salt and pepper.

title: spaghetti salad(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Toss with remaining ingredients (easier in large, flat baking pan).
Garnish with tomato wedges and paprika.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: vegetable medley casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento and 1/2 can fried onions.
Bake in covered casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.

title: sinfully rich nonfat fudge sauce
directions: In small saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa and cornstarch; gradually stir in evaporated milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly with whisk, until mixture boils; continue cooking and stirring until thickened and smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or cold with assorted fresh fruit, cake or nonfat frozen yogurt, if desired.
Cover; refrigerate leftover sauce.
Makes 7 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread.
Cut into cubes.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with sausage (and sauteed vegetables if desired).
Cover with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over bread. Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet red beets
directions: Cook beets with skins on until done.
Remove skins, slice or cut into pieces.

title: roasted tomato soup
directions: Arrange tomatoes on baking sheet, drizzle with 1/4 cup oil and sprinkle them with mixed garlic and thyme.
Roast at 350° for 1 hour, turning occasionally.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of 14-inch serving dish.
Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and water; simmer for 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over refried beans.
Arrange layers of lettuce, salsa or picante and cheese on top of meat. Garnish with desired toppings and serve with tortilla chips. Makes 14 to 16 appetizer servings.

title: strawberry banana shortcake(a classic dessert, but with bananas added!)
directions: In large mixing bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.
Spread dough in greased 8 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pan, slightly building up edges.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack 3 minutes.
With serrated knife, slit in two layers, lifting top off carefully.
Spread bottom layer with additional butter.
Combine strawberries and bananas.
Whip cream until soft peaks form.
Spoon fruits, then whipped cream between shortcake layers and over top.
Garnish with additional strawberries, if desired.
To serve, cut in 6 wedges.

title: 3 day beef brisket
directions: First Day:
Sprinkle beef with celery and onion salts.
Place in large pan lined with heavy-duty foil (large enough to tightly fold).
Add 1/2 bottle of liquid smoke and refrigerate.

title: pickled okra
directions: Note:
Need 8 small mouth pint jars.

title: basic barbecue sauce
directions: Heat oil in a medium saucepan and cook the onion and garlic gently for 10 minutes.
Add the catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, chili powder and cayenne; mix well.
Let simmer for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened.
Brush on chicken or ribs during the last five to ten minutes of grilling.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: bundt pound cake
directions: Butter Bundt pan well.
Flour a little.
Cool in pan before turning out.
Cream butter and sugar with electric beater.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift soda with flour.
Alternately add flour/soda and sour cream.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours (check at 1 1/4 hours).

title: stuffed pumpkin
directions: Cut top off pumpkin; save top as lid. Clean inside of pumpkin removing seeds. Fill pumpkin with 1/3 seasoned bread crumbs, 1/3 shredded Swiss cheese and 1/3 cream.
Place it on a baking sheet. Bake for 45 minutes at 350° (only 30 minutes for smaller pumpkin). Set on the table with a serving spoon (it is its own bowl). Spoon out pumpkin meat with stuffing.

title: fruit cake muffins
directions: Coat fruit, nuts and coconut with cake mix in a large bowl. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Adjust time for smaller muffins.
Makes 36 (2 1/2-inch) muffins.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° and then 25 minutes at 350°.
